   5952 </a><a href="#h4-0-853" id="h4-0-853" class="i">+  inputs.position = (uViewMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   5953 </a><a href="#h4-0-854" id="h4-0-854" class="i">+  inputs.normal = uCameraNormalMatrix * inputs.normal;
   5954 </a><a href="#h4-0-855" id="h4-0-855" class="i">+#else
   5955 </a><a href="#h4-0-856" id="h4-0-856" class="i">+  // Apply both at once
   5956 </a><a href="#h4-0-857" id="h4-0-857" class="i">+  inputs.position = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   5957 </a><a href="#h4-0-858" id="h4-0-858" class="i">+  inputs.normal = uNormalMatrix * inputs.normal;
   5958 </a><a href="#h4-0-859" id="h4-0-859" class="i">+#endif
   5959 </a><a href="#h4-0-860" id="h4-0-860" class="i">+#ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getCameraInputs
   5960 </a><a href="#h4-0-861" id="h4-0-861" class="i">+  inputs = HOOK_getCameraInputs(inputs);
   5961 </a><a href="#h4-0-862" id="h4-0-862" class="i">+#endif
   5962 </a><a href="#h4-0-863" id="h4-0-863" class="i">+
   5963 </a><a href="#h4-0-864" id="h4-0-864" class="i">+  // Pass varyings to fragment shader
   5964 </a><a href="#h4-0-865" id="h4-0-865" class="i">+  vViewPosition = inputs.position;
   5965 </a><a href="#h4-0-866" id="h4-0-866" class="i">+  vTexCoord = inputs.texCoord;
   5966 </a><a href="#h4-0-867" id="h4-0-867" class="i">+  vNormal = inputs.normal;
   5967 </a><a href="#h4-0-868" id="h4-0-868" class="i">+  vColor = inputs.color;
   5968 </a><a href="#h4-0-869" id="h4-0-869" class="i">+
   5969 </a><a href="#h4-0-870" id="h4-0-870" class="i">+  // TODO: this should be a uniform
   5970 </a><a href="#h4-0-871" id="h4-0-871" class="i">+  vAmbientColor = vec3(0.0);
   5971 </a><a href="#h4-0-872" id="h4-0-872" class="i">+  for (int i = 0; i &lt; 5; i++) {
   5972 </a><a href="#h4-0-873" id="h4-0-873" class="i">+    if (i &lt; uAmbientLightCount) {
   5973 </a><a href="#h4-0-874" id="h4-0-874" class="i">+      vAmbientColor += uAmbientColor[i];
   5974 </a><a href="#h4-0-875" id="h4-0-875" class="i">+    }
   5975 </a><a href="#h4-0-876" id="h4-0-876" class="i">+  }
   5976 </a><a href="#h4-0-877" id="h4-0-877" class="i">+
   5977 </a><a href="#h4-0-878" id="h4-0-878" class="i">+  gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.);
   5978 </a><a href="#h4-0-879" id="h4-0-879" class="i">+  HOOK_afterVertex();
   5979 </a><a href="#h4-0-880" id="h4-0-880" class="i">+}
   5980 </a><a href="#h4-0-881" id="h4-0-881" class="i">+`,Sb=`// include lighting.glsl
   5981 </a><a href="#h4-0-882" id="h4-0-882" class="i">+precision highp int;
   5982 </a><a href="#h4-0-883" id="h4-0-883" class="i">+
   5983 </a><a href="#h4-0-884" id="h4-0-884" class="i">+uniform bool uHasSetAmbient;
   5984 </a><a href="#h4-0-885" id="h4-0-885" class="i">+uniform vec4 uSpecularMatColor;
   5985 </a><a href="#h4-0-886" id="h4-0-886" class="i">+uniform vec4 uAmbientMatColor;
   5986 </a><a href="#h4-0-887" id="h4-0-887" class="i">+uniform vec4 uEmissiveMatColor;
   5987 </a><a href="#h4-0-888" id="h4-0-888" class="i">+
   5988 </a><a href="#h4-0-889" id="h4-0-889" class="i">+uniform vec4 uTint;
   5989 </a><a href="#h4-0-890" id="h4-0-890" class="i">+uniform sampler2D uSampler;
   5990 </a><a href="#h4-0-891" id="h4-0-891" class="i">+uniform bool isTexture;
   5991 </a><a href="#h4-0-892" id="h4-0-892" class="i">+
   5992 </a><a href="#h4-0-893" id="h4-0-893" class="i">+IN vec3 vNormal;
   5993 </a><a href="#h4-0-894" id="h4-0-894" class="i">+IN vec2 vTexCoord;
   5994 </a><a href="#h4-0-895" id="h4-0-895" class="i">+IN vec3 vViewPosition;
   5995 </a><a href="#h4-0-896" id="h4-0-896" class="i">+IN vec3 vAmbientColor;
   5996 </a><a href="#h4-0-897" id="h4-0-897" class="i">+IN vec4 vColor;
   5997 </a><a href="#h4-0-898" id="h4-0-898" class="i">+
   5998 </a><a href="#h4-0-899" id="h4-0-899" class="i">+struct ColorComponents {
   5999 </a><a href="#h4-0-900" id="h4-0-900" class="i">+  vec3 baseColor;
   6000 </a><a href="#h4-0-901" id="h4-0-901" class="i">+  float opacity;
   6001 </a><a href="#h4-0-902" id="h4-0-902" class="i">+  vec3 ambientColor;
   6002 </a><a href="#h4-0-903" id="h4-0-903" class="i">+  vec3 specularColor;
   6003 </a><a href="#h4-0-904" id="h4-0-904" class="i">+  vec3 diffuse;
   6004 </a><a href="#h4-0-905" id="h4-0-905" class="i">+  vec3 ambient;
   6005 </a><a href="#h4-0-906" id="h4-0-906" class="i">+  vec3 specular;
   6006 </a><a href="#h4-0-907" id="h4-0-907" class="i">+  vec3 emissive;
   6007 </a><a href="#h4-0-908" id="h4-0-908" class="i">+};
   6008 </a><a href="#h4-0-909" id="h4-0-909" class="i">+
   6009 </a><a href="#h4-0-910" id="h4-0-910" class="i">+struct Inputs {
   6010 </a><a href="#h4-0-911" id="h4-0-911" class="i">+  vec3 normal;
   6011 </a><a href="#h4-0-912" id="h4-0-912" class="i">+  vec2 texCoord;
   6012 </a><a href="#h4-0-913" id="h4-0-913" class="i">+  vec3 ambientLight;
   6013 </a><a href="#h4-0-914" id="h4-0-914" class="i">+  vec3 ambientMaterial;
   6014 </a><a href="#h4-0-915" id="h4-0-915" class="i">+  vec3 specularMaterial;
   6015 </a><a href="#h4-0-916" id="h4-0-916" class="i">+  vec3 emissiveMaterial;
   6016 </a><a href="#h4-0-917" id="h4-0-917" class="i">+  vec4 color;
   6017 </a><a href="#h4-0-918" id="h4-0-918" class="i">+  float shininess;
   6018 </a><a href="#h4-0-919" id="h4-0-919" class="i">+  float metalness;
   6019 </a><a href="#h4-0-920" id="h4-0-920" class="i">+};
   6020 </a><a href="#h4-0-921" id="h4-0-921" class="i">+
   6021 </a><a href="#h4-0-922" id="h4-0-922" class="i">+void main(void) {
   6022 </a><a href="#h4-0-923" id="h4-0-923" class="i">+  HOOK_beforeFragment();
   6023 </a><a href="#h4-0-924" id="h4-0-924" class="i">+
   6024 </a><a href="#h4-0-925" id="h4-0-925" class="i">+  Inputs inputs;
   6025 </a><a href="#h4-0-926" id="h4-0-926" class="i">+  inputs.normal = normalize(vNormal);
   6026 </a><a href="#h4-0-927" id="h4-0-927" class="i">+  inputs.texCoord = vTexCoord;
   6027 </a><a href="#h4-0-928" id="h4-0-928" class="i">+  inputs.ambientLight = vAmbientColor;
   6028 </a><a href="#h4-0-929" id="h4-0-929" class="i">+  inputs.color = isTexture
   6029 </a><a href="#h4-0-930" id="h4-0-930" class="i">+      ? TEXTURE(uSampler, vTexCoord) * (vec4(uTint.rgb/255., 1.) * uTint.a/255.)
   6030 </a><a href="#h4-0-931" id="h4-0-931" class="i">+      : vColor;
   6031 </a><a href="#h4-0-932" id="h4-0-932" class="i">+  if (isTexture &amp;&amp; inputs.color.a &gt; 0.0) {
   6032 </a><a href="#h4-0-933" id="h4-0-933" class="i">+    // Textures come in with premultiplied alpha. Temporarily unpremultiply it
   6033 </a><a href="#h4-0-934" id="h4-0-934" class="i">+    // so hooks users don&#39;t have to think about premultiplied alpha.
   6034 </a><a href="#h4-0-935" id="h4-0-935" class="i">+    inputs.color.rgb /= inputs.color.a;
   6035 </a><a href="#h4-0-936" id="h4-0-936" class="i">+  }
   6036 </a><a href="#h4-0-937" id="h4-0-937" class="i">+  inputs.shininess = uShininess;
   6037 </a><a href="#h4-0-938" id="h4-0-938" class="i">+  inputs.metalness = uMetallic;
   6038 </a><a href="#h4-0-939" id="h4-0-939" class="i">+  inputs.ambientMaterial = uHasSetAmbient ? uAmbientMatColor.rgb : inputs.color.rgb;
   6039 </a><a href="#h4-0-940" id="h4-0-940" class="i">+  inputs.specularMaterial = uSpecularMatColor.rgb;
   6040 </a><a href="#h4-0-941" id="h4-0-941" class="i">+  inputs.emissiveMaterial = uEmissiveMatColor.rgb;
   6041 </a><a href="#h4-0-942" id="h4-0-942" class="i">+  inputs = HOOK_getPixelInputs(inputs);
   6042 </a><a href="#h4-0-943" id="h4-0-943" class="i">+
   6043 </a><a href="#h4-0-944" id="h4-0-944" class="i">+  vec3 diffuse;
   6044 </a><a href="#h4-0-945" id="h4-0-945" class="i">+  vec3 specular;
   6045 </a><a href="#h4-0-946" id="h4-0-946" class="i">+  totalLight(vViewPosition, inputs.normal, inputs.shininess, inputs.metalness, diffuse, specular);
   6046 </a><a href="#h4-0-947" id="h4-0-947" class="i">+
   6047 </a><a href="#h4-0-948" id="h4-0-948" class="i">+  // Calculating final color as result of all lights (plus emissive term).
   6048 </a><a href="#h4-0-949" id="h4-0-949" class="i">+
   6049 </a><a href="#h4-0-950" id="h4-0-950" class="i">+  vec2 texCoord = inputs.texCoord;
   6050 </a><a href="#h4-0-951" id="h4-0-951" class="i">+  vec4 baseColor = inputs.color;
   6051 </a><a href="#h4-0-952" id="h4-0-952" class="i">+  ColorComponents c;
   6052 </a><a href="#h4-0-953" id="h4-0-953" class="i">+  c.opacity = baseColor.a;
   6053 </a><a href="#h4-0-954" id="h4-0-954" class="i">+  c.baseColor = baseColor.rgb;
   6054 </a><a href="#h4-0-955" id="h4-0-955" class="i">+  c.ambientColor = inputs.ambientMaterial;
   6055 </a><a href="#h4-0-956" id="h4-0-956" class="i">+  c.specularColor = inputs.specularMaterial;
   6056 </a><a href="#h4-0-957" id="h4-0-957" class="i">+  c.diffuse = diffuse;
   6057 </a><a href="#h4-0-958" id="h4-0-958" class="i">+  c.ambient = inputs.ambientLight;
   6058 </a><a href="#h4-0-959" id="h4-0-959" class="i">+  c.specular = specular;
   6059 </a><a href="#h4-0-960" id="h4-0-960" class="i">+  c.emissive = inputs.emissiveMaterial;
   6060 </a><a href="#h4-0-961" id="h4-0-961" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR = HOOK_getFinalColor(HOOK_combineColors(c));
   6061 </a><a href="#h4-0-962" id="h4-0-962" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR.rgb *= OUT_COLOR.a; // Premultiply alpha before rendering
   6062 </a><a href="#h4-0-963" id="h4-0-963" class="i">+  HOOK_afterFragment();
   6063 </a><a href="#h4-0-964" id="h4-0-964" class="i">+}
   6064 </a><a href="#h4-0-965" id="h4-0-965" class="i">+`,Ab=`IN vec3 aPosition;
   6065 </a><a href="#h4-0-966" id="h4-0-966" class="i">+IN vec2 aTexCoord;
   6066 </a><a href="#h4-0-967" id="h4-0-967" class="i">+uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   6067 </a><a href="#h4-0-968" id="h4-0-968" class="i">+uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   6068 </a><a href="#h4-0-969" id="h4-0-969" class="i">+
   6069 </a><a href="#h4-0-970" id="h4-0-970" class="i">+uniform vec4 uGlyphRect;
   6070 </a><a href="#h4-0-971" id="h4-0-971" class="i">+uniform float uGlyphOffset;
   6071 </a><a href="#h4-0-972" id="h4-0-972" class="i">+
   6072 </a><a href="#h4-0-973" id="h4-0-973" class="i">+OUT vec2 vTexCoord;
   6073 </a><a href="#h4-0-974" id="h4-0-974" class="i">+OUT float w;
   6074 </a><a href="#h4-0-975" id="h4-0-975" class="i">+
   6075 </a><a href="#h4-0-976" id="h4-0-976" class="i">+void main() {
   6076 </a><a href="#h4-0-977" id="h4-0-977" class="i">+  vec4 positionVec4 = vec4(aPosition, 1.0);
   6077 </a><a href="#h4-0-978" id="h4-0-978" class="i">+
   6078 </a><a href="#h4-0-979" id="h4-0-979" class="i">+  // scale by the size of the glyph&#39;s rectangle
   6079 </a><a href="#h4-0-980" id="h4-0-980" class="i">+  positionVec4.xy *= uGlyphRect.zw - uGlyphRect.xy;
   6080 </a><a href="#h4-0-981" id="h4-0-981" class="i">+
   6081 </a><a href="#h4-0-982" id="h4-0-982" class="i">+  // Expand glyph bounding boxes by 1px on each side to give a bit of room
   6082 </a><a href="#h4-0-983" id="h4-0-983" class="i">+  // for antialiasing
   6083 </a><a href="#h4-0-984" id="h4-0-984" class="i">+  vec3 newOrigin = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(0., 0., 0., 1.)).xyz;
   6084 </a><a href="#h4-0-985" id="h4-0-985" class="i">+  vec3 newDX = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(1., 0., 0., 1.)).xyz;
   6085 </a><a href="#h4-0-986" id="h4-0-986" class="i">+  vec3 newDY = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(0., 1., 0., 1.)).xyz;
   6086 </a><a href="#h4-0-987" id="h4-0-987" class="i">+  vec2 pixelScale = vec2(
   6087 </a><a href="#h4-0-988" id="h4-0-988" class="i">+    1. / length(newOrigin - newDX),
   6088 </a><a href="#h4-0-989" id="h4-0-989" class="i">+    1. / length(newOrigin - newDY)
   6089 </a><a href="#h4-0-990" id="h4-0-990" class="i">+  );
   6090 </a><a href="#h4-0-991" id="h4-0-991" class="i">+  vec2 offset = pixelScale * normalize(aTexCoord - vec2(0.5, 0.5));
   6091 </a><a href="#h4-0-992" id="h4-0-992" class="i">+  vec2 textureOffset = offset * (1. / vec2(
   6092 </a><a href="#h4-0-993" id="h4-0-993" class="i">+    uGlyphRect.z - uGlyphRect.x,
   6093 </a><a href="#h4-0-994" id="h4-0-994" class="i">+    uGlyphRect.w - uGlyphRect.y
   6094 </a><a href="#h4-0-995" id="h4-0-995" class="i">+  ));
   6095 </a><a href="#h4-0-996" id="h4-0-996" class="i">+
   6096 </a><a href="#h4-0-997" id="h4-0-997" class="i">+  // move to the corner of the glyph
   6097 </a><a href="#h4-0-998" id="h4-0-998" class="i">+  positionVec4.xy += uGlyphRect.xy;
   6098 </a><a href="#h4-0-999" id="h4-0-999" class="i">+
   6099 </a><a href="#h4-0-1000" id="h4-0-1000" class="i">+  // move to the letter&#39;s line offset
   6100 </a><a href="#h4-0-1001" id="h4-0-1001" class="i">+  positionVec4.x += uGlyphOffset;
   6101 </a><a href="#h4-0-1002" id="h4-0-1002" class="i">+
   6102 </a><a href="#h4-0-1003" id="h4-0-1003" class="i">+  positionVec4.xy += offset;
   6103 </a><a href="#h4-0-1004" id="h4-0-1004" class="i">+  
   6104 </a><a href="#h4-0-1005" id="h4-0-1005" class="i">+  gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * uModelViewMatrix * positionVec4;
   6105 </a><a href="#h4-0-1006" id="h4-0-1006" class="i">+  vTexCoord = aTexCoord + textureOffset;
   6106 </a><a href="#h4-0-1007" id="h4-0-1007" class="i">+  w = gl_Position.w;
   6107 </a><a href="#h4-0-1008" id="h4-0-1008" class="i">+}
   6108 </a><a href="#h4-0-1009" id="h4-0-1009" class="i">+`,Db=`#ifndef WEBGL2
   6109 </a><a href="#h4-0-1010" id="h4-0-1010" class="i">+#extension GL_OES_standard_derivatives : enable
   6110 </a><a href="#h4-0-1011" id="h4-0-1011" class="i">+#endif
   6111 </a><a href="#h4-0-1012" id="h4-0-1012" class="i">+
   6112 </a><a href="#h4-0-1013" id="h4-0-1013" class="i">+#if 0
   6113 </a><a href="#h4-0-1014" id="h4-0-1014" class="i">+  // simulate integer math using floats
   6114 </a><a href="#h4-0-1015" id="h4-0-1015" class="i">+	#define int float
   6115 </a><a href="#h4-0-1016" id="h4-0-1016" class="i">+	#define ivec2 vec2
   6116 </a><a href="#h4-0-1017" id="h4-0-1017" class="i">+	#define INT(x) float(x)
   6117 </a><a href="#h4-0-1018" id="h4-0-1018" class="i">+
   6118 </a><a href="#h4-0-1019" id="h4-0-1019" class="i">+	int ifloor(float v) { return floor(v); }
   6119 </a><a href="#h4-0-1020" id="h4-0-1020" class="i">+	ivec2 ifloor(vec2 v) { return floor(v); }
   6120 </a><a href="#h4-0-1021" id="h4-0-1021" class="i">+
   6121 </a><a href="#h4-0-1022" id="h4-0-1022" class="i">+#else
   6122 </a><a href="#h4-0-1023" id="h4-0-1023" class="i">+  // use native integer math
   6123 </a><a href="#h4-0-1024" id="h4-0-1024" class="i">+	precision highp int;
   6124 </a><a href="#h4-0-1025" id="h4-0-1025" class="i">+	#define INT(x) x
   6125 </a><a href="#h4-0-1026" id="h4-0-1026" class="i">+
   6126 </a><a href="#h4-0-1027" id="h4-0-1027" class="i">+	int ifloor(float v) { return int(v); }
   6127 </a><a href="#h4-0-1028" id="h4-0-1028" class="i">+	int ifloor(int v) { return v; }
   6128 </a><a href="#h4-0-1029" id="h4-0-1029" class="i">+	ivec2 ifloor(vec2 v) { return ivec2(v); }
   6129 </a><a href="#h4-0-1030" id="h4-0-1030" class="i">+
   6130 </a><a href="#h4-0-1031" id="h4-0-1031" class="i">+#endif
   6131 </a><a href="#h4-0-1032" id="h4-0-1032" class="i">+
   6132 </a><a href="#h4-0-1033" id="h4-0-1033" class="i">+uniform sampler2D uSamplerStrokes;
   6133 </a><a href="#h4-0-1034" id="h4-0-1034" class="i">+uniform sampler2D uSamplerRowStrokes;
   6134 </a><a href="#h4-0-1035" id="h4-0-1035" class="i">+uniform sampler2D uSamplerRows;
   6135 </a><a href="#h4-0-1036" id="h4-0-1036" class="i">+uniform sampler2D uSamplerColStrokes;
   6136 </a><a href="#h4-0-1037" id="h4-0-1037" class="i">+uniform sampler2D uSamplerCols;
   6137 </a><a href="#h4-0-1038" id="h4-0-1038" class="i">+
   6138 </a><a href="#h4-0-1039" id="h4-0-1039" class="i">+uniform ivec2 uStrokeImageSize;
   6139 </a><a href="#h4-0-1040" id="h4-0-1040" class="i">+uniform ivec2 uCellsImageSize;
   6140 </a><a href="#h4-0-1041" id="h4-0-1041" class="i">+uniform ivec2 uGridImageSize;
   6141 </a><a href="#h4-0-1042" id="h4-0-1042" class="i">+
   6142 </a><a href="#h4-0-1043" id="h4-0-1043" class="i">+uniform ivec2 uGridOffset;
   6143 </a><a href="#h4-0-1044" id="h4-0-1044" class="i">+uniform ivec2 uGridSize;
   6144 </a><a href="#h4-0-1045" id="h4-0-1045" class="i">+uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   6145 </a><a href="#h4-0-1046" id="h4-0-1046" class="i">+
   6146 </a><a href="#h4-0-1047" id="h4-0-1047" class="i">+IN vec2 vTexCoord;
   6147 </a><a href="#h4-0-1048" id="h4-0-1048" class="i">+
   6148 </a><a href="#h4-0-1049" id="h4-0-1049" class="i">+// some helper functions
   6149 </a><a href="#h4-0-1050" id="h4-0-1050" class="i">+int ROUND(float v) { return ifloor(v + 0.5); }
   6150 </a><a href="#h4-0-1051" id="h4-0-1051" class="i">+ivec2 ROUND(vec2 v) { return ifloor(v + 0.5); }
   6151 </a><a href="#h4-0-1052" id="h4-0-1052" class="i">+float saturate(float v) { return clamp(v, 0.0, 1.0); }
   6152 </a><a href="#h4-0-1053" id="h4-0-1053" class="i">+vec2 saturate(vec2 v) { return clamp(v, 0.0, 1.0); }
   6153 </a><a href="#h4-0-1054" id="h4-0-1054" class="i">+
   6154 </a><a href="#h4-0-1055" id="h4-0-1055" class="i">+int mul(float v1, int v2) {
   6155 </a><a href="#h4-0-1056" id="h4-0-1056" class="i">+  return ifloor(v1 * float(v2));
   6156 </a><a href="#h4-0-1057" id="h4-0-1057" class="i">+}
   6157 </a><a href="#h4-0-1058" id="h4-0-1058" class="i">+
   6158 </a><a href="#h4-0-1059" id="h4-0-1059" class="i">+ivec2 mul(vec2 v1, ivec2 v2) {
   6159 </a><a href="#h4-0-1060" id="h4-0-1060" class="i">+  return ifloor(v1 * vec2(v2) + 0.5);
   6160 </a><a href="#h4-0-1061" id="h4-0-1061" class="i">+}
   6161 </a><a href="#h4-0-1062" id="h4-0-1062" class="i">+
   6162 </a><a href="#h4-0-1063" id="h4-0-1063" class="i">+// unpack a 16-bit integer from a float vec2
   6163 </a><a href="#h4-0-1064" id="h4-0-1064" class="i">+int getInt16(vec2 v) {
   6164 </a><a href="#h4-0-1065" id="h4-0-1065" class="i">+  ivec2 iv = ROUND(v * 255.0);
   6165 </a><a href="#h4-0-1066" id="h4-0-1066" class="i">+  return iv.x * INT(128) + iv.y;
   6166 </a><a href="#h4-0-1067" id="h4-0-1067" class="i">+}
   6167 </a><a href="#h4-0-1068" id="h4-0-1068" class="i">+
   6168 </a><a href="#h4-0-1069" id="h4-0-1069" class="i">+vec2 pixelScale;
   6169 </a><a href="#h4-0-1070" id="h4-0-1070" class="i">+vec2 coverage = vec2(0.0);
   6170 </a><a href="#h4-0-1071" id="h4-0-1071" class="i">+vec2 weight = vec2(0.5);
   6171 </a><a href="#h4-0-1072" id="h4-0-1072" class="i">+const float minDistance = 1.0/8192.0;
   6172 </a><a href="#h4-0-1073" id="h4-0-1073" class="i">+const float hardness = 1.05; // amount of antialias
   6173 </a><a href="#h4-0-1074" id="h4-0-1074" class="i">+
   6174 </a><a href="#h4-0-1075" id="h4-0-1075" class="i">+// the maximum number of curves in a glyph
   6175 </a><a href="#h4-0-1076" id="h4-0-1076" class="i">+const int N = INT(250);
   6176 </a><a href="#h4-0-1077" id="h4-0-1077" class="i">+
   6177 </a><a href="#h4-0-1078" id="h4-0-1078" class="i">+// retrieves an indexed pixel from a sampler
   6178 </a><a href="#h4-0-1079" id="h4-0-1079" class="i">+vec4 getTexel(sampler2D sampler, int pos, ivec2 size) {
   6179 </a><a href="#h4-0-1080" id="h4-0-1080" class="i">+  int width = size.x;
   6180 </a><a href="#h4-0-1081" id="h4-0-1081" class="i">+  int y = ifloor(pos / width);
   6181 </a><a href="#h4-0-1082" id="h4-0-1082" class="i">+  int x = pos - y * width;  // pos % width
   6182 </a><a href="#h4-0-1083" id="h4-0-1083" class="i">+
   6183 </a><a href="#h4-0-1084" id="h4-0-1084" class="i">+  return TEXTURE(sampler, (vec2(x, y) + 0.5) / vec2(size));
   6184 </a><a href="#h4-0-1085" id="h4-0-1085" class="i">+}
   6185 </a><a href="#h4-0-1086" id="h4-0-1086" class="i">+
   6186 </a><a href="#h4-0-1087" id="h4-0-1087" class="i">+void calulateCrossings(vec2 p0, vec2 p1, vec2 p2, out vec2 C1, out vec2 C2) {
   6187 </a><a href="#h4-0-1088" id="h4-0-1088" class="i">+
   6188 </a><a href="#h4-0-1089" id="h4-0-1089" class="i">+  // get the coefficients of the quadratic in t
   6189 </a><a href="#h4-0-1090" id="h4-0-1090" class="i">+  vec2 a = p0 - p1 * 2.0 + p2;
   6190 </a><a href="#h4-0-1091" id="h4-0-1091" class="i">+  vec2 b = p0 - p1;
   6191 </a><a href="#h4-0-1092" id="h4-0-1092" class="i">+  vec2 c = p0 - vTexCoord;
   6192 </a><a href="#h4-0-1093" id="h4-0-1093" class="i">+
   6193 </a><a href="#h4-0-1094" id="h4-0-1094" class="i">+  // found out which values of &#39;t&#39; it crosses the axes
   6194 </a><a href="#h4-0-1095" id="h4-0-1095" class="i">+  vec2 surd = sqrt(max(vec2(0.0), b * b - a * c));
   6195 </a><a href="#h4-0-1096" id="h4-0-1096" class="i">+  vec2 t1 = ((b - surd) / a).yx;
   6196 </a><a href="#h4-0-1097" id="h4-0-1097" class="i">+  vec2 t2 = ((b + surd) / a).yx;
   6197 </a><a href="#h4-0-1098" id="h4-0-1098" class="i">+
   6198 </a><a href="#h4-0-1099" id="h4-0-1099" class="i">+  // approximate straight lines to avoid rounding errors
   6199 </a><a href="#h4-0-1100" id="h4-0-1100" class="i">+  if (abs(a.y) &lt; 0.001)
   6200 </a><a href="#h4-0-1101" id="h4-0-1101" class="i">+    t1.x = t2.x = c.y / (2.0 * b.y);
   6201 </a><a href="#h4-0-1102" id="h4-0-1102" class="i">+
   6202 </a><a href="#h4-0-1103" id="h4-0-1103" class="i">+  if (abs(a.x) &lt; 0.001)
   6203 </a><a href="#h4-0-1104" id="h4-0-1104" class="i">+    t1.y = t2.y = c.x / (2.0 * b.x);
   6204 </a><a href="#h4-0-1105" id="h4-0-1105" class="i">+
   6205 </a><a href="#h4-0-1106" id="h4-0-1106" class="i">+  // plug into quadratic formula to find the corrdinates of the crossings
   6206 </a><a href="#h4-0-1107" id="h4-0-1107" class="i">+  C1 = ((a * t1 - b * 2.0) * t1 + c) * pixelScale;
   6207 </a><a href="#h4-0-1108" id="h4-0-1108" class="i">+  C2 = ((a * t2 - b * 2.0) * t2 + c) * pixelScale;
   6208 </a><a href="#h4-0-1109" id="h4-0-1109" class="i">+}
   6209 </a><a href="#h4-0-1110" id="h4-0-1110" class="i">+
   6210 </a><a href="#h4-0-1111" id="h4-0-1111" class="i">+void coverageX(vec2 p0, vec2 p1, vec2 p2) {
   6211 </a><a href="#h4-0-1112" id="h4-0-1112" class="i">+
   6212 </a><a href="#h4-0-1113" id="h4-0-1113" class="i">+  vec2 C1, C2;
   6213 </a><a href="#h4-0-1114" id="h4-0-1114" class="i">+  calulateCrossings(p0, p1, p2, C1, C2);
   6214 </a><a href="#h4-0-1115" id="h4-0-1115" class="i">+
   6215 </a><a href="#h4-0-1116" id="h4-0-1116" class="i">+  // determine on which side of the x-axis the points lie
   6216 </a><a href="#h4-0-1117" id="h4-0-1117" class="i">+  bool y0 = p0.y &gt; vTexCoord.y;
   6217 </a><a href="#h4-0-1118" id="h4-0-1118" class="i">+  bool y1 = p1.y &gt; vTexCoord.y;
   6218 </a><a href="#h4-0-1119" id="h4-0-1119" class="i">+  bool y2 = p2.y &gt; vTexCoord.y;
   6219 </a><a href="#h4-0-1120" id="h4-0-1120" class="i">+
   6220 </a><a href="#h4-0-1121" id="h4-0-1121" class="i">+  // could web be under the curve (after t1)?
   6221 </a><a href="#h4-0-1122" id="h4-0-1122" class="i">+  if (y1 ? !y2 : y0) {
   6222 </a><a href="#h4-0-1123" id="h4-0-1123" class="i">+    // add the coverage for t1
   6223 </a><a href="#h4-0-1124" id="h4-0-1124" class="i">+    coverage.x += saturate(C1.x + 0.5);
   6224 </a><a href="#h4-0-1125" id="h4-0-1125" class="i">+    // calculate the anti-aliasing for t1
   6225 </a><a href="#h4-0-1126" id="h4-0-1126" class="i">+    weight.x = min(weight.x, abs(C1.x));
   6226 </a><a href="#h4-0-1127" id="h4-0-1127" class="i">+  }
   6227 </a><a href="#h4-0-1128" id="h4-0-1128" class="i">+
   6228 </a><a href="#h4-0-1129" id="h4-0-1129" class="i">+  // are we outside the curve (after t2)?
   6229 </a><a href="#h4-0-1130" id="h4-0-1130" class="i">+  if (y1 ? !y0 : y2) {
   6230 </a><a href="#h4-0-1131" id="h4-0-1131" class="i">+    // subtract the coverage for t2
   6231 </a><a href="#h4-0-1132" id="h4-0-1132" class="i">+    coverage.x -= saturate(C2.x + 0.5);
   6232 </a><a href="#h4-0-1133" id="h4-0-1133" class="i">+    // calculate the anti-aliasing for t2
   6233 </a><a href="#h4-0-1134" id="h4-0-1134" class="i">+    weight.x = min(weight.x, abs(C2.x));
   6234 </a><a href="#h4-0-1135" id="h4-0-1135" class="i">+  }
   6235 </a><a href="#h4-0-1136" id="h4-0-1136" class="i">+}
   6236 </a><a href="#h4-0-1137" id="h4-0-1137" class="i">+
   6237 </a><a href="#h4-0-1138" id="h4-0-1138" class="i">+// this is essentially the same as coverageX, but with the axes swapped
   6238 </a><a href="#h4-0-1139" id="h4-0-1139" class="i">+void coverageY(vec2 p0, vec2 p1, vec2 p2) {
   6239 </a><a href="#h4-0-1140" id="h4-0-1140" class="i">+
   6240 </a><a href="#h4-0-1141" id="h4-0-1141" class="i">+  vec2 C1, C2;
   6241 </a><a href="#h4-0-1142" id="h4-0-1142" class="i">+  calulateCrossings(p0, p1, p2, C1, C2);
   6242 </a><a href="#h4-0-1143" id="h4-0-1143" class="i">+
   6243 </a><a href="#h4-0-1144" id="h4-0-1144" class="i">+  bool x0 = p0.x &gt; vTexCoord.x;
   6244 </a><a href="#h4-0-1145" id="h4-0-1145" class="i">+  bool x1 = p1.x &gt; vTexCoord.x;
   6245 </a><a href="#h4-0-1146" id="h4-0-1146" class="i">+  bool x2 = p2.x &gt; vTexCoord.x;
   6246 </a><a href="#h4-0-1147" id="h4-0-1147" class="i">+
   6247 </a><a href="#h4-0-1148" id="h4-0-1148" class="i">+  if (x1 ? !x2 : x0) {
   6248 </a><a href="#h4-0-1149" id="h4-0-1149" class="i">+    coverage.y -= saturate(C1.y + 0.5);
   6249 </a><a href="#h4-0-1150" id="h4-0-1150" class="i">+    weight.y = min(weight.y, abs(C1.y));
   6250 </a><a href="#h4-0-1151" id="h4-0-1151" class="i">+  }
   6251 </a><a href="#h4-0-1152" id="h4-0-1152" class="i">+
   6252 </a><a href="#h4-0-1153" id="h4-0-1153" class="i">+  if (x1 ? !x0 : x2) {
   6253 </a><a href="#h4-0-1154" id="h4-0-1154" class="i">+    coverage.y += saturate(C2.y + 0.5);
   6254 </a><a href="#h4-0-1155" id="h4-0-1155" class="i">+    weight.y = min(weight.y, abs(C2.y));
   6255 </a><a href="#h4-0-1156" id="h4-0-1156" class="i">+  }
   6256 </a><a href="#h4-0-1157" id="h4-0-1157" class="i">+}
   6257 </a><a href="#h4-0-1158" id="h4-0-1158" class="i">+
   6258 </a><a href="#h4-0-1159" id="h4-0-1159" class="i">+void main() {
   6259 </a><a href="#h4-0-1160" id="h4-0-1160" class="i">+
   6260 </a><a href="#h4-0-1161" id="h4-0-1161" class="i">+  // calculate the pixel scale based on screen-coordinates
   6261 </a><a href="#h4-0-1162" id="h4-0-1162" class="i">+  pixelScale = hardness / fwidth(vTexCoord);
   6262 </a><a href="#h4-0-1163" id="h4-0-1163" class="i">+
   6263 </a><a href="#h4-0-1164" id="h4-0-1164" class="i">+  // which grid cell is this pixel in?
   6264 </a><a href="#h4-0-1165" id="h4-0-1165" class="i">+  ivec2 gridCoord = ifloor(vTexCoord * vec2(uGridSize));
   6265 </a><a href="#h4-0-1166" id="h4-0-1166" class="i">+
   6266 </a><a href="#h4-0-1167" id="h4-0-1167" class="i">+  // intersect curves in this row
   6267 </a><a href="#h4-0-1168" id="h4-0-1168" class="i">+  {
   6268 </a><a href="#h4-0-1169" id="h4-0-1169" class="i">+    // the index into the row info bitmap
   6269 </a><a href="#h4-0-1170" id="h4-0-1170" class="i">+    int rowIndex = gridCoord.y + uGridOffset.y;
   6270 </a><a href="#h4-0-1171" id="h4-0-1171" class="i">+    // fetch the info texel
   6271 </a><a href="#h4-0-1172" id="h4-0-1172" class="i">+    vec4 rowInfo = getTexel(uSamplerRows, rowIndex, uGridImageSize);
   6272 </a><a href="#h4-0-1173" id="h4-0-1173" class="i">+    // unpack the rowInfo
   6273 </a><a href="#h4-0-1174" id="h4-0-1174" class="i">+    int rowStrokeIndex = getInt16(rowInfo.xy);
   6274 </a><a href="#h4-0-1175" id="h4-0-1175" class="i">+    int rowStrokeCount = getInt16(rowInfo.zw);
   6275 </a><a href="#h4-0-1176" id="h4-0-1176" class="i">+
   6276 </a><a href="#h4-0-1177" id="h4-0-1177" class="i">+    for (int iRowStroke = INT(0); iRowStroke &lt; N; iRowStroke++) {
   6277 </a><a href="#h4-0-1178" id="h4-0-1178" class="i">+      if (iRowStroke &gt;= rowStrokeCount)
   6278 </a><a href="#h4-0-1179" id="h4-0-1179" class="i">+        break;
   6279 </a><a href="#h4-0-1180" id="h4-0-1180" class="i">+
   6280 </a><a href="#h4-0-1181" id="h4-0-1181" class="i">+      // each stroke is made up of 3 points: the start and control point
   6281 </a><a href="#h4-0-1182" id="h4-0-1182" class="i">+      // and the start of the next curve.
   6282 </a><a href="#h4-0-1183" id="h4-0-1183" class="i">+      // fetch the indices of this pair of strokes:
   6283 </a><a href="#h4-0-1184" id="h4-0-1184" class="i">+      vec4 strokeIndices = getTexel(uSamplerRowStrokes, rowStrokeIndex++, uCellsImageSize);
   6284 </a><a href="#h4-0-1185" id="h4-0-1185" class="i">+
   6285 </a><a href="#h4-0-1186" id="h4-0-1186" class="i">+      // unpack the stroke index
   6286 </a><a href="#h4-0-1187" id="h4-0-1187" class="i">+      int strokePos = getInt16(strokeIndices.xy);
   6287 </a><a href="#h4-0-1188" id="h4-0-1188" class="i">+
   6288 </a><a href="#h4-0-1189" id="h4-0-1189" class="i">+      // fetch the two strokes
   6289 </a><a href="#h4-0-1190" id="h4-0-1190" class="i">+      vec4 stroke0 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(0), uStrokeImageSize);
   6290 </a><a href="#h4-0-1191" id="h4-0-1191" class="i">+      vec4 stroke1 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(1), uStrokeImageSize);
   6291 </a><a href="#h4-0-1192" id="h4-0-1192" class="i">+
   6292 </a><a href="#h4-0-1193" id="h4-0-1193" class="i">+      // calculate the coverage
   6293 </a><a href="#h4-0-1194" id="h4-0-1194" class="i">+      coverageX(stroke0.xy, stroke0.zw, stroke1.xy);
   6294 </a><a href="#h4-0-1195" id="h4-0-1195" class="i">+    }
   6295 </a><a href="#h4-0-1196" id="h4-0-1196" class="i">+  }
   6296 </a><a href="#h4-0-1197" id="h4-0-1197" class="i">+
   6297 </a><a href="#h4-0-1198" id="h4-0-1198" class="i">+  // intersect curves in this column
   6298 </a><a href="#h4-0-1199" id="h4-0-1199" class="i">+  {
   6299 </a><a href="#h4-0-1200" id="h4-0-1200" class="i">+    int colIndex = gridCoord.x + uGridOffset.x;
   6300 </a><a href="#h4-0-1201" id="h4-0-1201" class="i">+    vec4 colInfo = getTexel(uSamplerCols, colIndex, uGridImageSize);
   6301 </a><a href="#h4-0-1202" id="h4-0-1202" class="i">+    int colStrokeIndex = getInt16(colInfo.xy);
   6302 </a><a href="#h4-0-1203" id="h4-0-1203" class="i">+    int colStrokeCount = getInt16(colInfo.zw);
   6303 </a><a href="#h4-0-1204" id="h4-0-1204" class="i">+    
   6304 </a><a href="#h4-0-1205" id="h4-0-1205" class="i">+    for (int iColStroke = INT(0); iColStroke &lt; N; iColStroke++) {
   6305 </a><a href="#h4-0-1206" id="h4-0-1206" class="i">+      if (iColStroke &gt;= colStrokeCount)
   6306 </a><a href="#h4-0-1207" id="h4-0-1207" class="i">+        break;
   6307 </a><a href="#h4-0-1208" id="h4-0-1208" class="i">+
   6308 </a><a href="#h4-0-1209" id="h4-0-1209" class="i">+      vec4 strokeIndices = getTexel(uSamplerColStrokes, colStrokeIndex++, uCellsImageSize);
   6309 </a><a href="#h4-0-1210" id="h4-0-1210" class="i">+
   6310 </a><a href="#h4-0-1211" id="h4-0-1211" class="i">+      int strokePos = getInt16(strokeIndices.xy);
   6311 </a><a href="#h4-0-1212" id="h4-0-1212" class="i">+      vec4 stroke0 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(0), uStrokeImageSize);
   6312 </a><a href="#h4-0-1213" id="h4-0-1213" class="i">+      vec4 stroke1 = getTexel(uSamplerStrokes, strokePos + INT(1), uStrokeImageSize);
   6313 </a><a href="#h4-0-1214" id="h4-0-1214" class="i">+      coverageY(stroke0.xy, stroke0.zw, stroke1.xy);
   6314 </a><a href="#h4-0-1215" id="h4-0-1215" class="i">+    }
   6315 </a><a href="#h4-0-1216" id="h4-0-1216" class="i">+  }
   6316 </a><a href="#h4-0-1217" id="h4-0-1217" class="i">+
   6317 </a><a href="#h4-0-1218" id="h4-0-1218" class="i">+  weight = saturate(1.0 - weight * 2.0);
   6318 </a><a href="#h4-0-1219" id="h4-0-1219" class="i">+  float distance = max(weight.x + weight.y, minDistance); // manhattan approx.
   6319 </a><a href="#h4-0-1220" id="h4-0-1220" class="i">+  float antialias = abs(dot(coverage, weight) / distance);
   6320 </a><a href="#h4-0-1221" id="h4-0-1221" class="i">+  float cover = min(abs(coverage.x), abs(coverage.y));
   6321 </a><a href="#h4-0-1222" id="h4-0-1222" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR = vec4(uMaterialColor.rgb, 1.) * uMaterialColor.a;
   6322 </a><a href="#h4-0-1223" id="h4-0-1223" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR *= saturate(max(antialias, cover));
   6323 </a><a href="#h4-0-1224" id="h4-0-1224" class="i">+}
   6324 </a><a href="#h4-0-1225" id="h4-0-1225" class="i">+`,Fb=`/*
   6325 </a><a href="#h4-0-1226" id="h4-0-1226" class="i">+  Part of the Processing project - http://processing.org
   6326 </a><a href="#h4-0-1227" id="h4-0-1227" class="i">+  Copyright (c) 2012-15 The Processing Foundation
   6327 </a><a href="#h4-0-1228" id="h4-0-1228" class="i">+  Copyright (c) 2004-12 Ben Fry and Casey Reas
   6328 </a><a href="#h4-0-1229" id="h4-0-1229" class="i">+  Copyright (c) 2001-04 Massachusetts Institute of Technology
   6329 </a><a href="#h4-0-1230" id="h4-0-1230" class="i">+  This library is free software; you can redistribute it and/or
   6330 </a><a href="#h4-0-1231" id="h4-0-1231" class="i">+  modify it under the terms of the GNU Lesser General Public
   6331 </a><a href="#h4-0-1232" id="h4-0-1232" class="i">+  License as published by the Free Software Foundation, version 2.1.
   6332 </a><a href="#h4-0-1233" id="h4-0-1233" class="i">+  This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
   6333 </a><a href="#h4-0-1234" id="h4-0-1234" class="i">+  but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
   6334 </a><a href="#h4-0-1235" id="h4-0-1235" class="i">+  MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.  See the GNU
   6335 </a><a href="#h4-0-1236" id="h4-0-1236" class="i">+  Lesser General Public License for more details.
   6336 </a><a href="#h4-0-1237" id="h4-0-1237" class="i">+  You should have received a copy of the GNU Lesser General
   6337 </a><a href="#h4-0-1238" id="h4-0-1238" class="i">+  Public License along with this library; if not, write to the
   6338 </a><a href="#h4-0-1239" id="h4-0-1239" class="i">+  Free Software Foundation, Inc., 59 Temple Place, Suite 330,
   6339 </a><a href="#h4-0-1240" id="h4-0-1240" class="i">+  Boston, MA  02111-1307  USA
   6340 </a><a href="#h4-0-1241" id="h4-0-1241" class="i">+*/
   6341 </a><a href="#h4-0-1242" id="h4-0-1242" class="i">+
   6342 </a><a href="#h4-0-1243" id="h4-0-1243" class="i">+#define PROCESSING_LINE_SHADER
   6343 </a><a href="#h4-0-1244" id="h4-0-1244" class="i">+
   6344 </a><a href="#h4-0-1245" id="h4-0-1245" class="i">+#define HOOK_DEFINES
   6345 </a><a href="#h4-0-1246" id="h4-0-1246" class="i">+
   6346 </a><a href="#h4-0-1247" id="h4-0-1247" class="i">+precision highp int;
   6347 </a><a href="#h4-0-1248" id="h4-0-1248" class="i">+precision highp float;
   6348 </a><a href="#h4-0-1249" id="h4-0-1249" class="i">+
   6349 </a><a href="#h4-0-1250" id="h4-0-1250" class="i">+#ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getWorldInputs
   6350 </a><a href="#h4-0-1251" id="h4-0-1251" class="i">+uniform mat4 uModelMatrix;
   6351 </a><a href="#h4-0-1252" id="h4-0-1252" class="i">+uniform mat4 uViewMatrix;
   6352 </a><a href="#h4-0-1253" id="h4-0-1253" class="i">+#else
   6353 </a><a href="#h4-0-1254" id="h4-0-1254" class="i">+uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   6354 </a><a href="#h4-0-1255" id="h4-0-1255" class="i">+#endif
   6355 </a><a href="#h4-0-1256" id="h4-0-1256" class="i">+
   6356 </a><a href="#h4-0-1257" id="h4-0-1257" class="i">+uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   6357 </a><a href="#h4-0-1258" id="h4-0-1258" class="i">+uniform float uStrokeWeight;
   6358 </a><a href="#h4-0-1259" id="h4-0-1259" class="i">+
   6359 </a><a href="#h4-0-1260" id="h4-0-1260" class="i">+uniform bool uUseLineColor;
   6360 </a><a href="#h4-0-1261" id="h4-0-1261" class="i">+uniform bool uSimpleLines;
   6361 </a><a href="#h4-0-1262" id="h4-0-1262" class="i">+uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   6362 </a><a href="#h4-0-1263" id="h4-0-1263" class="i">+
   6363 </a><a href="#h4-0-1264" id="h4-0-1264" class="i">+uniform vec4 uViewport;
   6364 </a><a href="#h4-0-1265" id="h4-0-1265" class="i">+uniform int uPerspective;
   6365 </a><a href="#h4-0-1266" id="h4-0-1266" class="i">+uniform int uStrokeJoin;
   6366 </a><a href="#h4-0-1267" id="h4-0-1267" class="i">+
   6367 </a><a href="#h4-0-1268" id="h4-0-1268" class="i">+IN vec3 aPosition;
   6368 </a><a href="#h4-0-1269" id="h4-0-1269" class="i">+IN vec3 aTangentIn;
   6369 </a><a href="#h4-0-1270" id="h4-0-1270" class="i">+IN vec3 aTangentOut;
   6370 </a><a href="#h4-0-1271" id="h4-0-1271" class="i">+IN float aSide;
   6371 </a><a href="#h4-0-1272" id="h4-0-1272" class="i">+IN vec4 aVertexColor;
   6372 </a><a href="#h4-0-1273" id="h4-0-1273" class="i">+
   6373 </a><a href="#h4-0-1274" id="h4-0-1274" class="i">+OUT vec4 vColor;
   6374 </a><a href="#h4-0-1275" id="h4-0-1275" class="i">+OUT vec2 vTangent;
   6375 </a><a href="#h4-0-1276" id="h4-0-1276" class="i">+OUT vec2 vCenter;
   6376 </a><a href="#h4-0-1277" id="h4-0-1277" class="i">+OUT vec2 vPosition;
   6377 </a><a href="#h4-0-1278" id="h4-0-1278" class="i">+OUT float vMaxDist;
   6378 </a><a href="#h4-0-1279" id="h4-0-1279" class="i">+OUT float vCap;
   6379 </a><a href="#h4-0-1280" id="h4-0-1280" class="i">+OUT float vJoin;
   6380 </a><a href="#h4-0-1281" id="h4-0-1281" class="i">+OUT float vStrokeWeight;
   6381 </a><a href="#h4-0-1282" id="h4-0-1282" class="i">+
   6382 </a><a href="#h4-0-1283" id="h4-0-1283" class="i">+vec2 lineIntersection(vec2 aPoint, vec2 aDir, vec2 bPoint, vec2 bDir) {
   6383 </a><a href="#h4-0-1284" id="h4-0-1284" class="i">+  // Rotate and translate so a starts at the origin and goes out to the right
   6384 </a><a href="#h4-0-1285" id="h4-0-1285" class="i">+  bPoint -= aPoint;
   6385 </a><a href="#h4-0-1286" id="h4-0-1286" class="i">+  vec2 rotatedBFrom = vec2(
   6386 </a><a href="#h4-0-1287" id="h4-0-1287" class="i">+    bPoint.x*aDir.x + bPoint.y*aDir.y,
   6387 </a><a href="#h4-0-1288" id="h4-0-1288" class="i">+    bPoint.y*aDir.x - bPoint.x*aDir.y
   6388 </a><a href="#h4-0-1289" id="h4-0-1289" class="i">+  );
   6389 </a><a href="#h4-0-1290" id="h4-0-1290" class="i">+  vec2 bTo = bPoint + bDir;
   6390 </a><a href="#h4-0-1291" id="h4-0-1291" class="i">+  vec2 rotatedBTo = vec2(
   6391 </a><a href="#h4-0-1292" id="h4-0-1292" class="i">+    bTo.x*aDir.x + bTo.y*aDir.y,
   6392 </a><a href="#h4-0-1293" id="h4-0-1293" class="i">+    bTo.y*aDir.x - bTo.x*aDir.y
   6393 </a><a href="#h4-0-1294" id="h4-0-1294" class="i">+  );
   6394 </a><a href="#h4-0-1295" id="h4-0-1295" class="i">+  float intersectionDistance =
   6395 </a><a href="#h4-0-1296" id="h4-0-1296" class="i">+    rotatedBTo.x + (rotatedBFrom.x - rotatedBTo.x) * rotatedBTo.y /
   6396 </a><a href="#h4-0-1297" id="h4-0-1297" class="i">+    (rotatedBTo.y - rotatedBFrom.y);
   6397 </a><a href="#h4-0-1298" id="h4-0-1298" class="i">+  return aPoint + aDir * intersectionDistance;
   6398 </a><a href="#h4-0-1299" id="h4-0-1299" class="i">+}
   6399 </a><a href="#h4-0-1300" id="h4-0-1300" class="i">+
   6400 </a><a href="#h4-0-1301" id="h4-0-1301" class="i">+struct StrokeVertex {
   6401 </a><a href="#h4-0-1302" id="h4-0-1302" class="i">+  vec3 position;
   6402 </a><a href="#h4-0-1303" id="h4-0-1303" class="i">+  vec3 tangentIn;
   6403 </a><a href="#h4-0-1304" id="h4-0-1304" class="i">+  vec3 tangentOut;
   6404 </a><a href="#h4-0-1305" id="h4-0-1305" class="i">+  vec4 color;
   6405 </a><a href="#h4-0-1306" id="h4-0-1306" class="i">+  float weight;
   6406 </a><a href="#h4-0-1307" id="h4-0-1307" class="i">+};
   6407 </a><a href="#h4-0-1308" id="h4-0-1308" class="i">+
   6408 </a><a href="#h4-0-1309" id="h4-0-1309" class="i">+void main() {
   6409 </a><a href="#h4-0-1310" id="h4-0-1310" class="i">+  HOOK_beforeVertex();
   6410 </a><a href="#h4-0-1311" id="h4-0-1311" class="i">+
   6411 </a><a href="#h4-0-1312" id="h4-0-1312" class="i">+  if (!uSimpleLines) {
   6412 </a><a href="#h4-0-1313" id="h4-0-1313" class="i">+      // Caps have one of either the in or out tangent set to 0
   6413 </a><a href="#h4-0-1314" id="h4-0-1314" class="i">+      vCap = (aTangentIn == vec3(0.)) != (aTangentOut == vec3(0.)) ? 1. : 0.;
   6414 </a><a href="#h4-0-1315" id="h4-0-1315" class="i">+
   6415 </a><a href="#h4-0-1316" id="h4-0-1316" class="i">+      // Joins have two unique, defined tangents
   6416 </a><a href="#h4-0-1317" id="h4-0-1317" class="i">+      vJoin = (
   6417 </a><a href="#h4-0-1318" id="h4-0-1318" class="i">+          aTangentIn != vec3(0.) &amp;&amp;
   6418 </a><a href="#h4-0-1319" id="h4-0-1319" class="i">+          aTangentOut != vec3(0.) &amp;&amp;
   6419 </a><a href="#h4-0-1320" id="h4-0-1320" class="i">+          aTangentIn != aTangentOut
   6420 </a><a href="#h4-0-1321" id="h4-0-1321" class="i">+      ) ? 1. : 0.;
   6421 </a><a href="#h4-0-1322" id="h4-0-1322" class="i">+  }
   6422 </a><a href="#h4-0-1323" id="h4-0-1323" class="i">+
   6423 </a><a href="#h4-0-1324" id="h4-0-1324" class="i">+  StrokeVertex inputs;
   6424 </a><a href="#h4-0-1325" id="h4-0-1325" class="i">+  inputs.position = aPosition.xyz;
   6425 </a><a href="#h4-0-1326" id="h4-0-1326" class="i">+  inputs.color = uUseLineColor ? aVertexColor : uMaterialColor;
   6426 </a><a href="#h4-0-1327" id="h4-0-1327" class="i">+  inputs.weight = uStrokeWeight;
   6427 </a><a href="#h4-0-1328" id="h4-0-1328" class="i">+  inputs.tangentIn = aTangentIn;
   6428 </a><a href="#h4-0-1329" id="h4-0-1329" class="i">+  inputs.tangentOut = aTangentOut;
   6429 </a><a href="#h4-0-1330" id="h4-0-1330" class="i">+
   6430 </a><a href="#h4-0-1331" id="h4-0-1331" class="i">+#ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getObjectInputs
   6431 </a><a href="#h4-0-1332" id="h4-0-1332" class="i">+  inputs = HOOK_getObjectInputs(inputs);
   6432 </a><a href="#h4-0-1333" id="h4-0-1333" class="i">+#endif
   6433 </a><a href="#h4-0-1334" id="h4-0-1334" class="i">+
   6434 </a><a href="#h4-0-1335" id="h4-0-1335" class="i">+#ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getWorldInputs
   6435 </a><a href="#h4-0-1336" id="h4-0-1336" class="i">+  inputs.position = (uModelMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   6436 </a><a href="#h4-0-1337" id="h4-0-1337" class="i">+  inputs.tangentIn = (uModelMatrix * vec4(aTangentIn, 0.)).xyz;
   6437 </a><a href="#h4-0-1338" id="h4-0-1338" class="i">+  inputs.tangentOut = (uModelMatrix * vec4(aTangentOut, 0.)).xyz;
   6438 </a><a href="#h4-0-1339" id="h4-0-1339" class="i">+  inputs = HOOK_getWorldInputs(inputs);
   6439 </a><a href="#h4-0-1340" id="h4-0-1340" class="i">+#endif
   6440 </a><a href="#h4-0-1341" id="h4-0-1341" class="i">+
   6441 </a><a href="#h4-0-1342" id="h4-0-1342" class="i">+#ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getWorldInputs
   6442 </a><a href="#h4-0-1343" id="h4-0-1343" class="i">+  // Already multiplied by the model matrix, just apply view
   6443 </a><a href="#h4-0-1344" id="h4-0-1344" class="i">+  inputs.position = (uViewMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   6444 </a><a href="#h4-0-1345" id="h4-0-1345" class="i">+  inputs.tangentIn = (uViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentIn, 0.)).xyz;
   6445 </a><a href="#h4-0-1346" id="h4-0-1346" class="i">+  inputs.tangentOut = (uViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentOut, 0.)).xyz;
   6446 </a><a href="#h4-0-1347" id="h4-0-1347" class="i">+#else
   6447 </a><a href="#h4-0-1348" id="h4-0-1348" class="i">+  // Apply both at once
   6448 </a><a href="#h4-0-1349" id="h4-0-1349" class="i">+  inputs.position = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(inputs.position, 1.)).xyz;
   6449 </a><a href="#h4-0-1350" id="h4-0-1350" class="i">+  inputs.tangentIn = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentIn, 0.)).xyz;
   6450 </a><a href="#h4-0-1351" id="h4-0-1351" class="i">+  inputs.tangentOut = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aTangentOut, 0.)).xyz;
   6451 </a><a href="#h4-0-1352" id="h4-0-1352" class="i">+#endif
   6452 </a><a href="#h4-0-1353" id="h4-0-1353" class="i">+#ifdef AUGMENTED_HOOK_getCameraInputs
   6453 </a><a href="#h4-0-1354" id="h4-0-1354" class="i">+  inputs = hook_getCameraInputs(inputs);
   6454 </a><a href="#h4-0-1355" id="h4-0-1355" class="i">+#endif
   6455 </a><a href="#h4-0-1356" id="h4-0-1356" class="i">+
   6456 </a><a href="#h4-0-1357" id="h4-0-1357" class="i">+  vec4 posp = vec4(inputs.position, 1.);
   6457 </a><a href="#h4-0-1358" id="h4-0-1358" class="i">+  vec4 posqIn = vec4(inputs.position + inputs.tangentIn, 1.);
   6458 </a><a href="#h4-0-1359" id="h4-0-1359" class="i">+  vec4 posqOut = vec4(inputs.position + inputs.tangentOut, 1.);
   6459 </a><a href="#h4-0-1360" id="h4-0-1360" class="i">+  vStrokeWeight = inputs.weight;
   6460 </a><a href="#h4-0-1361" id="h4-0-1361" class="i">+
   6461 </a><a href="#h4-0-1362" id="h4-0-1362" class="i">+  float facingCamera = pow(
   6462 </a><a href="#h4-0-1363" id="h4-0-1363" class="i">+    // The word space tangent&#39;s z value is 0 if it&#39;s facing the camera
   6463 </a><a href="#h4-0-1364" id="h4-0-1364" class="i">+    abs(normalize(posqIn-posp).z),
   6464 </a><a href="#h4-0-1365" id="h4-0-1365" class="i">+
   6465 </a><a href="#h4-0-1366" id="h4-0-1366" class="i">+    // Using pow() here to ramp \`facingCamera\` up from 0 to 1 really quickly
   6466 </a><a href="#h4-0-1367" id="h4-0-1367" class="i">+    // so most lines get scaled and don&#39;t get clipped
   6467 </a><a href="#h4-0-1368" id="h4-0-1368" class="i">+    0.25
   6468 </a><a href="#h4-0-1369" id="h4-0-1369" class="i">+  );
   6469 </a><a href="#h4-0-1370" id="h4-0-1370" class="i">+
   6470 </a><a href="#h4-0-1371" id="h4-0-1371" class="i">+  // Moving vertices slightly toward the camera
   6471 </a><a href="#h4-0-1372" id="h4-0-1372" class="i">+  // to avoid depth-fighting with the fill triangles.
   6472 </a><a href="#h4-0-1373" id="h4-0-1373" class="i">+  // A mix of scaling and offsetting is used based on distance
   6473 </a><a href="#h4-0-1374" id="h4-0-1374" class="i">+  // Discussion here:
   6474 </a><a href="#h4-0-1375" id="h4-0-1375" class="i">+  // https://github.com/processing/p5.js/issues/7200 
   6475 </a><a href="#h4-0-1376" id="h4-0-1376" class="i">+
   6476 </a><a href="#h4-0-1377" id="h4-0-1377" class="i">+  // using a scale &lt;1 moves the lines towards nearby camera
   6477 </a><a href="#h4-0-1378" id="h4-0-1378" class="i">+  // in order to prevent popping effects due to half of
   6478 </a><a href="#h4-0-1379" id="h4-0-1379" class="i">+  // the line disappearing behind the geometry faces.
   6479 </a><a href="#h4-0-1380" id="h4-0-1380" class="i">+  float zDistance = -posp.z; 
   6480 </a><a href="#h4-0-1381" id="h4-0-1381" class="i">+  float distanceFactor = smoothstep(0.0, 800.0, zDistance); 
   6481 </a><a href="#h4-0-1382" id="h4-0-1382" class="i">+  
   6482 </a><a href="#h4-0-1383" id="h4-0-1383" class="i">+  // Discussed here:
   6483 </a><a href="#h4-0-1384" id="h4-0-1384" class="i">+  // http://www.opengl.org/discussion_boards/ubbthreads.php?ubb=showflat&amp;Number=252848  
   6484 </a><a href="#h4-0-1385" id="h4-0-1385" class="i">+  float scale = mix(1., 0.995, facingCamera);
   6485 </a><a href="#h4-0-1386" id="h4-0-1386" class="i">+  float dynamicScale = mix(scale, 1.0, distanceFactor); // Closer = more scale, farther = less
   6486 </a><a href="#h4-0-1387" id="h4-0-1387" class="i">+
   6487 </a><a href="#h4-0-1388" id="h4-0-1388" class="i">+  posp.xyz = posp.xyz * dynamicScale;
   6488 </a><a href="#h4-0-1389" id="h4-0-1389" class="i">+  posqIn.xyz = posqIn.xyz * dynamicScale;
   6489 </a><a href="#h4-0-1390" id="h4-0-1390" class="i">+  posqOut.xyz = posqOut.xyz * dynamicScale;
   6490 </a><a href="#h4-0-1391" id="h4-0-1391" class="i">+
   6491 </a><a href="#h4-0-1392" id="h4-0-1392" class="i">+  // Moving vertices slightly toward camera when far away 
   6492 </a><a href="#h4-0-1393" id="h4-0-1393" class="i">+  // https://github.com/processing/p5.js/issues/6956 
   6493 </a><a href="#h4-0-1394" id="h4-0-1394" class="i">+  float zOffset = mix(0., -1., facingCamera);
   6494 </a><a href="#h4-0-1395" id="h4-0-1395" class="i">+  float dynamicZAdjustment = mix(0.0, zOffset, distanceFactor); // Closer = less zAdjustment, farther = more
   6495 </a><a href="#h4-0-1396" id="h4-0-1396" class="i">+
   6496 </a><a href="#h4-0-1397" id="h4-0-1397" class="i">+  posp.z -= dynamicZAdjustment;
   6497 </a><a href="#h4-0-1398" id="h4-0-1398" class="i">+  posqIn.z -= dynamicZAdjustment;
   6498 </a><a href="#h4-0-1399" id="h4-0-1399" class="i">+  posqOut.z -= dynamicZAdjustment;
   6499 </a><a href="#h4-0-1400" id="h4-0-1400" class="i">+  
   6500 </a><a href="#h4-0-1401" id="h4-0-1401" class="i">+  vec4 p = uProjectionMatrix * posp;
   6501 </a><a href="#h4-0-1402" id="h4-0-1402" class="i">+  vec4 qIn = uProjectionMatrix * posqIn;
   6502 </a><a href="#h4-0-1403" id="h4-0-1403" class="i">+  vec4 qOut = uProjectionMatrix * posqOut;
   6503 </a><a href="#h4-0-1404" id="h4-0-1404" class="i">+
   6504 </a><a href="#h4-0-1405" id="h4-0-1405" class="i">+  // formula to convert from clip space (range -1..1) to screen space (range 0..[width or height])
   6505 </a><a href="#h4-0-1406" id="h4-0-1406" class="i">+  // screen_p = (p.xy/p.w + &lt;1,1&gt;) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw
   6506 </a><a href="#h4-0-1407" id="h4-0-1407" class="i">+
   6507 </a><a href="#h4-0-1408" id="h4-0-1408" class="i">+  // prevent division by W by transforming the tangent formula (div by 0 causes
   6508 </a><a href="#h4-0-1409" id="h4-0-1409" class="i">+  // the line to disappear, see https://github.com/processing/processing/issues/5183)
   6509 </a><a href="#h4-0-1410" id="h4-0-1410" class="i">+  // t = screen_q - screen_p
   6510 </a><a href="#h4-0-1411" id="h4-0-1411" class="i">+  //
   6511 </a><a href="#h4-0-1412" id="h4-0-1412" class="i">+  // tangent is normalized and we don&#39;t care which aDirection it points to (+-)
   6512 </a><a href="#h4-0-1413" id="h4-0-1413" class="i">+  // t = +- normalize( screen_q - screen_p )
   6513 </a><a href="#h4-0-1414" id="h4-0-1414" class="i">+  // t = +- normalize( (q.xy/q.w+&lt;1,1&gt;)*0.5*uViewport.zw - (p.xy/p.w+&lt;1,1&gt;)*0.5*uViewport.zw )
   6514 </a><a href="#h4-0-1415" id="h4-0-1415" class="i">+  //
   6515 </a><a href="#h4-0-1416" id="h4-0-1416" class="i">+  // extract common factor, &lt;1,1&gt; - &lt;1,1&gt; cancels out
   6516 </a><a href="#h4-0-1417" id="h4-0-1417" class="i">+  // t = +- normalize( (q.xy/q.w - p.xy/p.w) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw )
   6517 </a><a href="#h4-0-1418" id="h4-0-1418" class="i">+  //
   6518 </a><a href="#h4-0-1419" id="h4-0-1419" class="i">+  // convert to common divisor
   6519 </a><a href="#h4-0-1420" id="h4-0-1420" class="i">+  // t = +- normalize( ((q.xy*p.w - p.xy*q.w) / (p.w*q.w)) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw )
   6520 </a><a href="#h4-0-1421" id="h4-0-1421" class="i">+  //
   6521 </a><a href="#h4-0-1422" id="h4-0-1422" class="i">+  // remove the common scalar divisor/factor, not needed due to normalize and +-
   6522 </a><a href="#h4-0-1423" id="h4-0-1423" class="i">+  // (keep uViewport - can&#39;t remove because it has different components for x and y
   6523 </a><a href="#h4-0-1424" id="h4-0-1424" class="i">+  //  and corrects for aspect ratio, see https://github.com/processing/processing/issues/5181)
   6524 </a><a href="#h4-0-1425" id="h4-0-1425" class="i">+  // t = +- normalize( (q.xy*p.w - p.xy*q.w) * uViewport.zw )
   6525 </a><a href="#h4-0-1426" id="h4-0-1426" class="i">+
   6526 </a><a href="#h4-0-1427" id="h4-0-1427" class="i">+  vec2 tangentIn = normalize((qIn.xy*p.w - p.xy*qIn.w) * uViewport.zw);
   6527 </a><a href="#h4-0-1428" id="h4-0-1428" class="i">+  vec2 tangentOut = normalize((qOut.xy*p.w - p.xy*qOut.w) * uViewport.zw);
   6528 </a><a href="#h4-0-1429" id="h4-0-1429" class="i">+
   6529 </a><a href="#h4-0-1430" id="h4-0-1430" class="i">+  vec2 curPerspScale;
   6530 </a><a href="#h4-0-1431" id="h4-0-1431" class="i">+  if(uPerspective == 1) {
   6531 </a><a href="#h4-0-1432" id="h4-0-1432" class="i">+    // Perspective ---
   6532 </a><a href="#h4-0-1433" id="h4-0-1433" class="i">+    // convert from world to clip by multiplying with projection scaling factor
   6533 </a><a href="#h4-0-1434" id="h4-0-1434" class="i">+    // to get the right thickness (see https://github.com/processing/processing/issues/5182)
   6534 </a><a href="#h4-0-1435" id="h4-0-1435" class="i">+
   6535 </a><a href="#h4-0-1436" id="h4-0-1436" class="i">+    // The y value of the projection matrix may be flipped if rendering to a Framebuffer.
   6536 </a><a href="#h4-0-1437" id="h4-0-1437" class="i">+    // Multiplying again by its sign here negates the flip to get just the scale.
   6537 </a><a href="#h4-0-1438" id="h4-0-1438" class="i">+    curPerspScale = (uProjectionMatrix * vec4(1, sign(uProjectionMatrix[1][1]), 0, 0)).xy;
   6538 </a><a href="#h4-0-1439" id="h4-0-1439" class="i">+  } else {
   6539 </a><a href="#h4-0-1440" id="h4-0-1440" class="i">+    // No Perspective ---
   6540 </a><a href="#h4-0-1441" id="h4-0-1441" class="i">+    // multiply by W (to cancel out division by W later in the pipeline) and
   6541 </a><a href="#h4-0-1442" id="h4-0-1442" class="i">+    // convert from screen to clip (derived from clip to screen above)
   6542 </a><a href="#h4-0-1443" id="h4-0-1443" class="i">+    curPerspScale = p.w / (0.5 * uViewport.zw);
   6543 </a><a href="#h4-0-1444" id="h4-0-1444" class="i">+  }
   6544 </a><a href="#h4-0-1445" id="h4-0-1445" class="i">+
   6545 </a><a href="#h4-0-1446" id="h4-0-1446" class="i">+  vec2 offset;
   6546 </a><a href="#h4-0-1447" id="h4-0-1447" class="i">+  if (vJoin == 1. &amp;&amp; !uSimpleLines) {
   6547 </a><a href="#h4-0-1448" id="h4-0-1448" class="i">+    vTangent = normalize(tangentIn + tangentOut);
   6548 </a><a href="#h4-0-1449" id="h4-0-1449" class="i">+    vec2 normalIn = vec2(-tangentIn.y, tangentIn.x);
   6549 </a><a href="#h4-0-1450" id="h4-0-1450" class="i">+    vec2 normalOut = vec2(-tangentOut.y, tangentOut.x);
   6550 </a><a href="#h4-0-1451" id="h4-0-1451" class="i">+    float side = sign(aSide);
   6551 </a><a href="#h4-0-1452" id="h4-0-1452" class="i">+    float sideEnum = abs(aSide);
   6552 </a><a href="#h4-0-1453" id="h4-0-1453" class="i">+
   6553 </a><a href="#h4-0-1454" id="h4-0-1454" class="i">+    // We generate vertices for joins on either side of the centerline, but
   6554 </a><a href="#h4-0-1455" id="h4-0-1455" class="i">+    // the &quot;elbow&quot; side is the only one needing a join. By not setting the
   6555 </a><a href="#h4-0-1456" id="h4-0-1456" class="i">+    // offset for the other side, all its vertices will end up in the same
   6556 </a><a href="#h4-0-1457" id="h4-0-1457" class="i">+    // spot and not render, effectively discarding it.
   6557 </a><a href="#h4-0-1458" id="h4-0-1458" class="i">+    if (sign(dot(tangentOut, vec2(-tangentIn.y, tangentIn.x))) != side) {
   6558 </a><a href="#h4-0-1459" id="h4-0-1459" class="i">+      // Side enums:
   6559 </a><a href="#h4-0-1460" id="h4-0-1460" class="i">+      //   1: the side going into the join
   6560 </a><a href="#h4-0-1461" id="h4-0-1461" class="i">+      //   2: the middle of the join
   6561 </a><a href="#h4-0-1462" id="h4-0-1462" class="i">+      //   3: the side going out of the join
   6562 </a><a href="#h4-0-1463" id="h4-0-1463" class="i">+      if (sideEnum == 2.) {
   6563 </a><a href="#h4-0-1464" id="h4-0-1464" class="i">+        // Calculate the position + tangent on either side of the join, and
   6564 </a><a href="#h4-0-1465" id="h4-0-1465" class="i">+        // find where the lines intersect to find the elbow of the join
   6565 </a><a href="#h4-0-1466" id="h4-0-1466" class="i">+        vec2 c = (posp.xy/posp.w + vec2(1.,1.)) * 0.5 * uViewport.zw;
   6566 </a><a href="#h4-0-1467" id="h4-0-1467" class="i">+        vec2 intersection = lineIntersection(
   6567 </a><a href="#h4-0-1468" id="h4-0-1468" class="i">+          c + (side * normalIn * inputs.weight / 2.),
   6568 </a><a href="#h4-0-1469" id="h4-0-1469" class="i">+          tangentIn,
   6569 </a><a href="#h4-0-1470" id="h4-0-1470" class="i">+          c + (side * normalOut * inputs.weight / 2.),
   6570 </a><a href="#h4-0-1471" id="h4-0-1471" class="i">+          tangentOut
   6571 </a><a href="#h4-0-1472" id="h4-0-1472" class="i">+        );
   6572 </a><a href="#h4-0-1473" id="h4-0-1473" class="i">+        offset = (intersection - c);
   6573 </a><a href="#h4-0-1474" id="h4-0-1474" class="i">+
   6574 </a><a href="#h4-0-1475" id="h4-0-1475" class="i">+        // When lines are thick and the angle of the join approaches 180, the
   6575 </a><a href="#h4-0-1476" id="h4-0-1476" class="i">+        // elbow might be really far from the center. We&#39;ll apply a limit to
   6576 </a><a href="#h4-0-1477" id="h4-0-1477" class="i">+        // the magnitude to avoid lines going across the whole screen when this
   6577 </a><a href="#h4-0-1478" id="h4-0-1478" class="i">+        // happens.
   6578 </a><a href="#h4-0-1479" id="h4-0-1479" class="i">+        float mag = length(offset);
   6579 </a><a href="#h4-0-1480" id="h4-0-1480" class="i">+        float maxMag = 3. * inputs.weight;
   6580 </a><a href="#h4-0-1481" id="h4-0-1481" class="i">+        if (mag &gt; maxMag) {
   6581 </a><a href="#h4-0-1482" id="h4-0-1482" class="i">+          offset *= maxMag / mag;
   6582 </a><a href="#h4-0-1483" id="h4-0-1483" class="i">+        }
   6583 </a><a href="#h4-0-1484" id="h4-0-1484" class="i">+      } else if (sideEnum == 1.) {
   6584 </a><a href="#h4-0-1485" id="h4-0-1485" class="i">+        offset = side * normalIn * inputs.weight / 2.;
   6585 </a><a href="#h4-0-1486" id="h4-0-1486" class="i">+      } else if (sideEnum == 3.) {
   6586 </a><a href="#h4-0-1487" id="h4-0-1487" class="i">+        offset = side * normalOut * inputs.weight / 2.;
   6587 </a><a href="#h4-0-1488" id="h4-0-1488" class="i">+      }
   6588 </a><a href="#h4-0-1489" id="h4-0-1489" class="i">+    }
   6589 </a><a href="#h4-0-1490" id="h4-0-1490" class="i">+    if (uStrokeJoin == STROKE_JOIN_BEVEL) {
   6590 </a><a href="#h4-0-1491" id="h4-0-1491" class="i">+      vec2 avgNormal = vec2(-vTangent.y, vTangent.x);
   6591 </a><a href="#h4-0-1492" id="h4-0-1492" class="i">+      vMaxDist = abs(dot(avgNormal, normalIn * inputs.weight / 2.));
   6592 </a><a href="#h4-0-1493" id="h4-0-1493" class="i">+    } else {
   6593 </a><a href="#h4-0-1494" id="h4-0-1494" class="i">+      vMaxDist = inputs.weight / 2.;
   6594 </a><a href="#h4-0-1495" id="h4-0-1495" class="i">+    }
   6595 </a><a href="#h4-0-1496" id="h4-0-1496" class="i">+  } else {
   6596 </a><a href="#h4-0-1497" id="h4-0-1497" class="i">+    vec2 tangent = aTangentIn == vec3(0.) ? tangentOut : tangentIn;
   6597 </a><a href="#h4-0-1498" id="h4-0-1498" class="i">+    vTangent = tangent;
   6598 </a><a href="#h4-0-1499" id="h4-0-1499" class="i">+    vec2 normal = vec2(-tangent.y, tangent.x);
   6599 </a><a href="#h4-0-1500" id="h4-0-1500" class="i">+
   6600 </a><a href="#h4-0-1501" id="h4-0-1501" class="i">+    float normalOffset = sign(aSide);
   6601 </a><a href="#h4-0-1502" id="h4-0-1502" class="i">+    // Caps will have side values of -2 or 2 on the edge of the cap that
   6602 </a><a href="#h4-0-1503" id="h4-0-1503" class="i">+    // extends out from the line
   6603 </a><a href="#h4-0-1504" id="h4-0-1504" class="i">+    float tangentOffset = abs(aSide) - 1.;
   6604 </a><a href="#h4-0-1505" id="h4-0-1505" class="i">+    offset = (normal * normalOffset + tangent * tangentOffset) *
   6605 </a><a href="#h4-0-1506" id="h4-0-1506" class="i">+      inputs.weight * 0.5;
   6606 </a><a href="#h4-0-1507" id="h4-0-1507" class="i">+    vMaxDist = inputs.weight / 2.;
   6607 </a><a href="#h4-0-1508" id="h4-0-1508" class="i">+  }
   6608 </a><a href="#h4-0-1509" id="h4-0-1509" class="i">+
   6609 </a><a href="#h4-0-1510" id="h4-0-1510" class="i">+  vCenter = p.xy;
   6610 </a><a href="#h4-0-1511" id="h4-0-1511" class="i">+  vPosition = vCenter + offset;
   6611 </a><a href="#h4-0-1512" id="h4-0-1512" class="i">+  vColor = inputs.color;
   6612 </a><a href="#h4-0-1513" id="h4-0-1513" class="i">+
   6613 </a><a href="#h4-0-1514" id="h4-0-1514" class="i">+  gl_Position.xy = p.xy + offset.xy * curPerspScale;
   6614 </a><a href="#h4-0-1515" id="h4-0-1515" class="i">+  gl_Position.zw = p.zw;
   6615 </a><a href="#h4-0-1516" id="h4-0-1516" class="i">+  
   6616 </a><a href="#h4-0-1517" id="h4-0-1517" class="i">+  HOOK_afterVertex();
   6617 </a><a href="#h4-0-1518" id="h4-0-1518" class="i">+}
   6618 </a><a href="#h4-0-1519" id="h4-0-1519" class="i">+`,Tb=`precision highp int;
   6619 </a><a href="#h4-0-1520" id="h4-0-1520" class="i">+precision highp float;
   6620 </a><a href="#h4-0-1521" id="h4-0-1521" class="i">+
   6621 </a><a href="#h4-0-1522" id="h4-0-1522" class="i">+uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   6622 </a><a href="#h4-0-1523" id="h4-0-1523" class="i">+uniform int uStrokeCap;
   6623 </a><a href="#h4-0-1524" id="h4-0-1524" class="i">+uniform int uStrokeJoin;
   6624 </a><a href="#h4-0-1525" id="h4-0-1525" class="i">+
   6625 </a><a href="#h4-0-1526" id="h4-0-1526" class="i">+IN vec4 vColor;
   6626 </a><a href="#h4-0-1527" id="h4-0-1527" class="i">+IN vec2 vTangent;
   6627 </a><a href="#h4-0-1528" id="h4-0-1528" class="i">+IN vec2 vCenter;
   6628 </a><a href="#h4-0-1529" id="h4-0-1529" class="i">+IN vec2 vPosition;
   6629 </a><a href="#h4-0-1530" id="h4-0-1530" class="i">+IN float vStrokeWeight;
   6630 </a><a href="#h4-0-1531" id="h4-0-1531" class="i">+IN float vMaxDist;
   6631 </a><a href="#h4-0-1532" id="h4-0-1532" class="i">+IN float vCap;
   6632 </a><a href="#h4-0-1533" id="h4-0-1533" class="i">+IN float vJoin;
   6633 </a><a href="#h4-0-1534" id="h4-0-1534" class="i">+
   6634 </a><a href="#h4-0-1535" id="h4-0-1535" class="i">+float distSquared(vec2 a, vec2 b) {
   6635 </a><a href="#h4-0-1536" id="h4-0-1536" class="i">+  vec2 aToB = b - a;
   6636 </a><a href="#h4-0-1537" id="h4-0-1537" class="i">+  return dot(aToB, aToB);
   6637 </a><a href="#h4-0-1538" id="h4-0-1538" class="i">+}
   6638 </a><a href="#h4-0-1539" id="h4-0-1539" class="i">+
   6639 </a><a href="#h4-0-1540" id="h4-0-1540" class="i">+struct Inputs {
   6640 </a><a href="#h4-0-1541" id="h4-0-1541" class="i">+  vec4 color;
   6641 </a><a href="#h4-0-1542" id="h4-0-1542" class="i">+  vec2 tangent;
   6642 </a><a href="#h4-0-1543" id="h4-0-1543" class="i">+  vec2 center;
   6643 </a><a href="#h4-0-1544" id="h4-0-1544" class="i">+  vec2 position;
   6644 </a><a href="#h4-0-1545" id="h4-0-1545" class="i">+  float strokeWeight;
   6645 </a><a href="#h4-0-1546" id="h4-0-1546" class="i">+};
   6646 </a><a href="#h4-0-1547" id="h4-0-1547" class="i">+
   6647 </a><a href="#h4-0-1548" id="h4-0-1548" class="i">+void main() {
   6648 </a><a href="#h4-0-1549" id="h4-0-1549" class="i">+  HOOK_beforeFragment();
   6649 </a><a href="#h4-0-1550" id="h4-0-1550" class="i">+
   6650 </a><a href="#h4-0-1551" id="h4-0-1551" class="i">+  Inputs inputs;
   6651 </a><a href="#h4-0-1552" id="h4-0-1552" class="i">+  inputs.color = vColor;
   6652 </a><a href="#h4-0-1553" id="h4-0-1553" class="i">+  inputs.tangent = vTangent;
   6653 </a><a href="#h4-0-1554" id="h4-0-1554" class="i">+  inputs.center = vCenter;
   6654 </a><a href="#h4-0-1555" id="h4-0-1555" class="i">+  inputs.position = vPosition;
   6655 </a><a href="#h4-0-1556" id="h4-0-1556" class="i">+  inputs.strokeWeight = vStrokeWeight;
   6656 </a><a href="#h4-0-1557" id="h4-0-1557" class="i">+  inputs = HOOK_getPixelInputs(inputs);
   6657 </a><a href="#h4-0-1558" id="h4-0-1558" class="i">+
   6658 </a><a href="#h4-0-1559" id="h4-0-1559" class="i">+  if (vCap &gt; 0.) {
   6659 </a><a href="#h4-0-1560" id="h4-0-1560" class="i">+    if (
   6660 </a><a href="#h4-0-1561" id="h4-0-1561" class="i">+      uStrokeCap == STROKE_CAP_ROUND &amp;&amp;
   6661 </a><a href="#h4-0-1562" id="h4-0-1562" class="i">+      HOOK_shouldDiscard(distSquared(inputs.position, inputs.center) &gt; inputs.strokeWeight * inputs.strokeWeight * 0.25)
   6662 </a><a href="#h4-0-1563" id="h4-0-1563" class="i">+    ) {
   6663 </a><a href="#h4-0-1564" id="h4-0-1564" class="i">+      discard;
   6664 </a><a href="#h4-0-1565" id="h4-0-1565" class="i">+    } else if (
   6665 </a><a href="#h4-0-1566" id="h4-0-1566" class="i">+      uStrokeCap == STROKE_CAP_SQUARE &amp;&amp;
   6666 </a><a href="#h4-0-1567" id="h4-0-1567" class="i">+      HOOK_shouldDiscard(dot(inputs.position - inputs.center, inputs.tangent) &gt; 0.)
   6667 </a><a href="#h4-0-1568" id="h4-0-1568" class="i">+    ) {
   6668 </a><a href="#h4-0-1569" id="h4-0-1569" class="i">+      discard;
   6669 </a><a href="#h4-0-1570" id="h4-0-1570" class="i">+    // Use full area for PROJECT
   6670 </a><a href="#h4-0-1571" id="h4-0-1571" class="i">+    } else if (HOOK_shouldDiscard(false)) {
   6671 </a><a href="#h4-0-1572" id="h4-0-1572" class="i">+      discard;
   6672 </a><a href="#h4-0-1573" id="h4-0-1573" class="i">+    }
   6673 </a><a href="#h4-0-1574" id="h4-0-1574" class="i">+  } else if (vJoin &gt; 0.) {
   6674 </a><a href="#h4-0-1575" id="h4-0-1575" class="i">+    if (
   6675 </a><a href="#h4-0-1576" id="h4-0-1576" class="i">+      uStrokeJoin == STROKE_JOIN_ROUND &amp;&amp;
   6676 </a><a href="#h4-0-1577" id="h4-0-1577" class="i">+      HOOK_shouldDiscard(distSquared(inputs.position, inputs.center) &gt; inputs.strokeWeight * inputs.strokeWeight * 0.25)
   6677 </a><a href="#h4-0-1578" id="h4-0-1578" class="i">+    ) {
   6678 </a><a href="#h4-0-1579" id="h4-0-1579" class="i">+      discard;
   6679 </a><a href="#h4-0-1580" id="h4-0-1580" class="i">+    } else if (uStrokeJoin == STROKE_JOIN_BEVEL) {
   6680 </a><a href="#h4-0-1581" id="h4-0-1581" class="i">+      vec2 normal = vec2(-inputs.tangent.y, inputs.tangent.x);
   6681 </a><a href="#h4-0-1582" id="h4-0-1582" class="i">+      if (HOOK_shouldDiscard(abs(dot(inputs.position - inputs.center, normal)) &gt; vMaxDist)) {
   6682 </a><a href="#h4-0-1583" id="h4-0-1583" class="i">+        discard;
   6683 </a><a href="#h4-0-1584" id="h4-0-1584" class="i">+      }
   6684 </a><a href="#h4-0-1585" id="h4-0-1585" class="i">+    // Use full area for MITER
   6685 </a><a href="#h4-0-1586" id="h4-0-1586" class="i">+    } else if (HOOK_shouldDiscard(false)) {
   6686 </a><a href="#h4-0-1587" id="h4-0-1587" class="i">+      discard;
   6687 </a><a href="#h4-0-1588" id="h4-0-1588" class="i">+    }
   6688 </a><a href="#h4-0-1589" id="h4-0-1589" class="i">+  }
   6689 </a><a href="#h4-0-1590" id="h4-0-1590" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR = HOOK_getFinalColor(vec4(inputs.color.rgb, 1.) * inputs.color.a);
   6690 </a><a href="#h4-0-1591" id="h4-0-1591" class="i">+  HOOK_afterFragment();
   6691 </a><a href="#h4-0-1592" id="h4-0-1592" class="i">+}
   6692 </a><a href="#h4-0-1593" id="h4-0-1593" class="i">+`,Nb=`IN vec3 aPosition;
   6693 </a><a href="#h4-0-1594" id="h4-0-1594" class="i">+uniform float uPointSize;
   6694 </a><a href="#h4-0-1595" id="h4-0-1595" class="i">+OUT float vStrokeWeight;
   6695 </a><a href="#h4-0-1596" id="h4-0-1596" class="i">+uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   6696 </a><a href="#h4-0-1597" id="h4-0-1597" class="i">+uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   6697 </a><a href="#h4-0-1598" id="h4-0-1598" class="i">+
   6698 </a><a href="#h4-0-1599" id="h4-0-1599" class="i">+void main() {
   6699 </a><a href="#h4-0-1600" id="h4-0-1600" class="i">+  HOOK_beforeVertex();
   6700 </a><a href="#h4-0-1601" id="h4-0-1601" class="i">+  vec4 viewModelPosition = vec4(HOOK_getWorldPosition(
   6701 </a><a href="#h4-0-1602" id="h4-0-1602" class="i">+    (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(HOOK_getLocalPosition(aPosition), 1.0)).xyz
   6702 </a><a href="#h4-0-1603" id="h4-0-1603" class="i">+  ), 1.);
   6703 </a><a href="#h4-0-1604" id="h4-0-1604" class="i">+  gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * viewModelPosition;  
   6704 </a><a href="#h4-0-1605" id="h4-0-1605" class="i">+
   6705 </a><a href="#h4-0-1606" id="h4-0-1606" class="i">+  float pointSize = HOOK_getPointSize(uPointSize);
   6706 </a><a href="#h4-0-1607" id="h4-0-1607" class="i">+
   6707 </a><a href="#h4-0-1608" id="h4-0-1608" class="i">+	gl_PointSize = pointSize;
   6708 </a><a href="#h4-0-1609" id="h4-0-1609" class="i">+	vStrokeWeight = pointSize;
   6709 </a><a href="#h4-0-1610" id="h4-0-1610" class="i">+  HOOK_afterVertex();
   6710 </a><a href="#h4-0-1611" id="h4-0-1611" class="i">+}
   6711 </a><a href="#h4-0-1612" id="h4-0-1612" class="i">+`,Ib=`precision mediump int;
   6712 </a><a href="#h4-0-1613" id="h4-0-1613" class="i">+uniform vec4 uMaterialColor;
   6713 </a><a href="#h4-0-1614" id="h4-0-1614" class="i">+IN float vStrokeWeight;
   6714 </a><a href="#h4-0-1615" id="h4-0-1615" class="i">+
   6715 </a><a href="#h4-0-1616" id="h4-0-1616" class="i">+void main(){
   6716 </a><a href="#h4-0-1617" id="h4-0-1617" class="i">+  HOOK_beforeFragment();
   6717 </a><a href="#h4-0-1618" id="h4-0-1618" class="i">+  float mask = 0.0;
   6718 </a><a href="#h4-0-1619" id="h4-0-1619" class="i">+
   6719 </a><a href="#h4-0-1620" id="h4-0-1620" class="i">+  // make a circular mask using the gl_PointCoord (goes from 0 - 1 on a point)
   6720 </a><a href="#h4-0-1621" id="h4-0-1621" class="i">+  // might be able to get a nicer edge on big strokeweights with smoothstep but slightly less performant
   6721 </a><a href="#h4-0-1622" id="h4-0-1622" class="i">+
   6722 </a><a href="#h4-0-1623" id="h4-0-1623" class="i">+  mask = step(0.98, length(gl_PointCoord * 2.0 - 1.0));
   6723 </a><a href="#h4-0-1624" id="h4-0-1624" class="i">+
   6724 </a><a href="#h4-0-1625" id="h4-0-1625" class="i">+  // if strokeWeight is 1 or less lets just draw a square
   6725 </a><a href="#h4-0-1626" id="h4-0-1626" class="i">+  // this prevents weird artifacting from carving circles when our points are really small
   6726 </a><a href="#h4-0-1627" id="h4-0-1627" class="i">+  // if strokeWeight is larger than 1, we just use it as is
   6727 </a><a href="#h4-0-1628" id="h4-0-1628" class="i">+
   6728 </a><a href="#h4-0-1629" id="h4-0-1629" class="i">+  mask = mix(0.0, mask, clamp(floor(vStrokeWeight - 0.5),0.0,1.0));
   6729 </a><a href="#h4-0-1630" id="h4-0-1630" class="i">+
   6730 </a><a href="#h4-0-1631" id="h4-0-1631" class="i">+  // throw away the borders of the mask
   6731 </a><a href="#h4-0-1632" id="h4-0-1632" class="i">+  // otherwise we get weird alpha blending issues
   6732 </a><a href="#h4-0-1633" id="h4-0-1633" class="i">+
   6733 </a><a href="#h4-0-1634" id="h4-0-1634" class="i">+  if(HOOK_shouldDiscard(mask &gt; 0.98)){
   6734 </a><a href="#h4-0-1635" id="h4-0-1635" class="i">+    discard;
   6735 </a><a href="#h4-0-1636" id="h4-0-1636" class="i">+  }
   6736 </a><a href="#h4-0-1637" id="h4-0-1637" class="i">+
   6737 </a><a href="#h4-0-1638" id="h4-0-1638" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR = HOOK_getFinalColor(vec4(uMaterialColor.rgb, 1.) * uMaterialColor.a);
   6738 </a><a href="#h4-0-1639" id="h4-0-1639" class="i">+  HOOK_afterFragment();
   6739 </a><a href="#h4-0-1640" id="h4-0-1640" class="i">+}
   6740 </a><a href="#h4-0-1641" id="h4-0-1641" class="i">+`,kb=`precision highp float;
   6741 </a><a href="#h4-0-1642" id="h4-0-1642" class="i">+attribute vec3 aPosition;
   6742 </a><a href="#h4-0-1643" id="h4-0-1643" class="i">+attribute vec3 aNormal;
   6743 </a><a href="#h4-0-1644" id="h4-0-1644" class="i">+attribute vec2 aTexCoord;
   6744 </a><a href="#h4-0-1645" id="h4-0-1645" class="i">+
   6745 </a><a href="#h4-0-1646" id="h4-0-1646" class="i">+varying vec3 localPos;
   6746 </a><a href="#h4-0-1647" id="h4-0-1647" class="i">+varying vec3 vWorldNormal;
   6747 </a><a href="#h4-0-1648" id="h4-0-1648" class="i">+varying vec3 vWorldPosition;
   6748 </a><a href="#h4-0-1649" id="h4-0-1649" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   6749 </a><a href="#h4-0-1650" id="h4-0-1650" class="i">+
   6750 </a><a href="#h4-0-1651" id="h4-0-1651" class="i">+uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   6751 </a><a href="#h4-0-1652" id="h4-0-1652" class="i">+uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   6752 </a><a href="#h4-0-1653" id="h4-0-1653" class="i">+uniform mat3 uNormalMatrix;
   6753 </a><a href="#h4-0-1654" id="h4-0-1654" class="i">+
   6754 </a><a href="#h4-0-1655" id="h4-0-1655" class="i">+void main() {
   6755 </a><a href="#h4-0-1656" id="h4-0-1656" class="i">+  // Multiply the position by the matrix.
   6756 </a><a href="#h4-0-1657" id="h4-0-1657" class="i">+  vec4 viewModelPosition = uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aPosition, 1.0);
   6757 </a><a href="#h4-0-1658" id="h4-0-1658" class="i">+  gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * viewModelPosition;  
   6758 </a><a href="#h4-0-1659" id="h4-0-1659" class="i">+  
   6759 </a><a href="#h4-0-1660" id="h4-0-1660" class="i">+  // orient the normals and pass to the fragment shader
   6760 </a><a href="#h4-0-1661" id="h4-0-1661" class="i">+  vWorldNormal = uNormalMatrix * aNormal;
   6761 </a><a href="#h4-0-1662" id="h4-0-1662" class="i">+  
   6762 </a><a href="#h4-0-1663" id="h4-0-1663" class="i">+  // send the view position to the fragment shader
   6763 </a><a href="#h4-0-1664" id="h4-0-1664" class="i">+  vWorldPosition = (uModelViewMatrix * vec4(aPosition, 1.0)).xyz;
   6764 </a><a href="#h4-0-1665" id="h4-0-1665" class="i">+  
   6765 </a><a href="#h4-0-1666" id="h4-0-1666" class="i">+  localPos = vWorldPosition;
   6766 </a><a href="#h4-0-1667" id="h4-0-1667" class="i">+  vTexCoord = aTexCoord;
   6767 </a><a href="#h4-0-1668" id="h4-0-1668" class="i">+}
   6768 </a><a href="#h4-0-1669" id="h4-0-1669" class="i">+
   6769 </a><a href="#h4-0-1670" id="h4-0-1670" class="i">+
   6770 </a><a href="#h4-0-1671" id="h4-0-1671" class="i">+/*
   6771 </a><a href="#h4-0-1672" id="h4-0-1672" class="i">+in the vertex shader we&#39;ll compute the world position and world oriented normal of the vertices and pass those to the fragment shader as varyings.
   6772 </a><a href="#h4-0-1673" id="h4-0-1673" class="i">+*/
   6773 </a><a href="#h4-0-1674" id="h4-0-1674" class="i">+`,Mb=`precision highp float;
   6774 </a><a href="#h4-0-1675" id="h4-0-1675" class="i">+varying vec3 localPos;
   6775 </a><a href="#h4-0-1676" id="h4-0-1676" class="i">+
   6776 </a><a href="#h4-0-1677" id="h4-0-1677" class="i">+// the HDR cubemap converted (can be from an equirectangular environment map.)
   6777 </a><a href="#h4-0-1678" id="h4-0-1678" class="i">+uniform sampler2D environmentMap;
   6778 </a><a href="#h4-0-1679" id="h4-0-1679" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   6779 </a><a href="#h4-0-1680" id="h4-0-1680" class="i">+
   6780 </a><a href="#h4-0-1681" id="h4-0-1681" class="i">+const float PI = 3.14159265359;
   6781 </a><a href="#h4-0-1682" id="h4-0-1682" class="i">+
   6782 </a><a href="#h4-0-1683" id="h4-0-1683" class="i">+vec2 nTOE( vec3 v ){
   6783 </a><a href="#h4-0-1684" id="h4-0-1684" class="i">+  // x = r sin(phi) cos(theta)   
   6784 </a><a href="#h4-0-1685" id="h4-0-1685" class="i">+  // y = r cos(phi)  
   6785 </a><a href="#h4-0-1686" id="h4-0-1686" class="i">+  // z = r sin(phi) sin(theta)
   6786 </a><a href="#h4-0-1687" id="h4-0-1687" class="i">+  float phi = acos( v.y );
   6787 </a><a href="#h4-0-1688" id="h4-0-1688" class="i">+  // if phi is 0, then there are no x, z components
   6788 </a><a href="#h4-0-1689" id="h4-0-1689" class="i">+  float theta = 0.0;
   6789 </a><a href="#h4-0-1690" id="h4-0-1690" class="i">+  // else 
   6790 </a><a href="#h4-0-1691" id="h4-0-1691" class="i">+  theta = acos(v.x / sin(phi));
   6791 </a><a href="#h4-0-1692" id="h4-0-1692" class="i">+  float sinTheta = v.z / sin(phi);
   6792 </a><a href="#h4-0-1693" id="h4-0-1693" class="i">+  if (sinTheta &lt; 0.0) {
   6793 </a><a href="#h4-0-1694" id="h4-0-1694" class="i">+    // Turn it into -theta, but in the 0-2PI range
   6794 </a><a href="#h4-0-1695" id="h4-0-1695" class="i">+    theta = 2.0 * PI - theta;
   6795 </a><a href="#h4-0-1696" id="h4-0-1696" class="i">+  }
   6796 </a><a href="#h4-0-1697" id="h4-0-1697" class="i">+  theta = theta / (2.0 * 3.14159);
   6797 </a><a href="#h4-0-1698" id="h4-0-1698" class="i">+  phi = phi / 3.14159 ;
   6798 </a><a href="#h4-0-1699" id="h4-0-1699" class="i">+  
   6799 </a><a href="#h4-0-1700" id="h4-0-1700" class="i">+  vec2 angles = vec2( phi, theta );
   6800 </a><a href="#h4-0-1701" id="h4-0-1701" class="i">+  return angles;
   6801 </a><a href="#h4-0-1702" id="h4-0-1702" class="i">+}
   6802 </a><a href="#h4-0-1703" id="h4-0-1703" class="i">+
   6803 </a><a href="#h4-0-1704" id="h4-0-1704" class="i">+float random(vec2 p) {
   6804 </a><a href="#h4-0-1705" id="h4-0-1705" class="i">+  vec3 p3  = fract(vec3(p.xyx) * .1031);
   6805 </a><a href="#h4-0-1706" id="h4-0-1706" class="i">+  p3 += dot(p3, p3.yzx + 33.33);
   6806 </a><a href="#h4-0-1707" id="h4-0-1707" class="i">+  return fract((p3.x + p3.y) * p3.z);
   6807 </a><a href="#h4-0-1708" id="h4-0-1708" class="i">+}
   6808 </a><a href="#h4-0-1709" id="h4-0-1709" class="i">+
   6809 </a><a href="#h4-0-1710" id="h4-0-1710" class="i">+void main()
   6810 </a><a href="#h4-0-1711" id="h4-0-1711" class="i">+{   	 
   6811 </a><a href="#h4-0-1712" id="h4-0-1712" class="i">+	// the sample direction equals the hemisphere&#39;s orientation
   6812 </a><a href="#h4-0-1713" id="h4-0-1713" class="i">+  float phi = vTexCoord.x * 2.0 * PI;
   6813 </a><a href="#h4-0-1714" id="h4-0-1714" class="i">+  float theta = vTexCoord.y * PI;
   6814 </a><a href="#h4-0-1715" id="h4-0-1715" class="i">+  float x = sin(theta) * cos(phi);
   6815 </a><a href="#h4-0-1716" id="h4-0-1716" class="i">+  float y = sin(theta) * sin(phi);
   6816 </a><a href="#h4-0-1717" id="h4-0-1717" class="i">+  float z = cos(theta);
   6817 </a><a href="#h4-0-1718" id="h4-0-1718" class="i">+  vec3 normal = vec3( x, y, z);
   6818 </a><a href="#h4-0-1719" id="h4-0-1719" class="i">+
   6819 </a><a href="#h4-0-1720" id="h4-0-1720" class="i">+	// Discretely sampling the hemisphere given the integral&#39;s
   6820 </a><a href="#h4-0-1721" id="h4-0-1721" class="i">+  // spherical coordinates translates to the following fragment code:
   6821 </a><a href="#h4-0-1722" id="h4-0-1722" class="i">+	vec3 irradiance = vec3(0.0);  
   6822 </a><a href="#h4-0-1723" id="h4-0-1723" class="i">+	vec3 up	= vec3(0.0, 1.0, 0.0);
   6823 </a><a href="#h4-0-1724" id="h4-0-1724" class="i">+	vec3 right = normalize(cross(up, normal));
   6824 </a><a href="#h4-0-1725" id="h4-0-1725" class="i">+	up = normalize(cross(normal, right));
   6825 </a><a href="#h4-0-1726" id="h4-0-1726" class="i">+
   6826 </a><a href="#h4-0-1727" id="h4-0-1727" class="i">+	//  We specify a fixed sampleDelta delta value to traverse
   6827 </a><a href="#h4-0-1728" id="h4-0-1728" class="i">+  // the hemisphere; decreasing or increasing the sample delta
   6828 </a><a href="#h4-0-1729" id="h4-0-1729" class="i">+  // will increase or decrease the accuracy respectively.
   6829 </a><a href="#h4-0-1730" id="h4-0-1730" class="i">+	const float sampleDelta = 0.100;
   6830 </a><a href="#h4-0-1731" id="h4-0-1731" class="i">+	float nrSamples = 0.0;
   6831 </a><a href="#h4-0-1732" id="h4-0-1732" class="i">+  float randomOffset = random(gl_FragCoord.xy) * sampleDelta;
   6832 </a><a href="#h4-0-1733" id="h4-0-1733" class="i">+	for(float rawPhi = 0.0; rawPhi &lt; 2.0 * PI; rawPhi += sampleDelta)
   6833 </a><a href="#h4-0-1734" id="h4-0-1734" class="i">+	{
   6834 </a><a href="#h4-0-1735" id="h4-0-1735" class="i">+    float phi = rawPhi + randomOffset;
   6835 </a><a href="#h4-0-1736" id="h4-0-1736" class="i">+    for(float rawTheta = 0.0; rawTheta &lt; ( 0.5 ) * PI; rawTheta += sampleDelta)
   6836 </a><a href="#h4-0-1737" id="h4-0-1737" class="i">+    {
   6837 </a><a href="#h4-0-1738" id="h4-0-1738" class="i">+      float theta = rawTheta + randomOffset;
   6838 </a><a href="#h4-0-1739" id="h4-0-1739" class="i">+      // spherical to cartesian (in tangent space) // tangent space to world // add each sample result to irradiance
   6839 </a><a href="#h4-0-1740" id="h4-0-1740" class="i">+      float x = sin(theta) * cos(phi);
   6840 </a><a href="#h4-0-1741" id="h4-0-1741" class="i">+      float y = sin(theta) * sin(phi);
   6841 </a><a href="#h4-0-1742" id="h4-0-1742" class="i">+      float z = cos(theta);
