   6842 </a><a href="#h4-0-1743" id="h4-0-1743" class="i">+      vec3 tangentSample = vec3( x, y, z);
   6843 </a><a href="#h4-0-1744" id="h4-0-1744" class="i">+      
   6844 </a><a href="#h4-0-1745" id="h4-0-1745" class="i">+      vec3 sampleVec = tangentSample.x * right + tangentSample.y * up + tangentSample.z * normal;
   6845 </a><a href="#h4-0-1746" id="h4-0-1746" class="i">+        irradiance += (texture2D(environmentMap, nTOE(sampleVec)).xyz) * cos(theta) * sin(theta);
   6846 </a><a href="#h4-0-1747" id="h4-0-1747" class="i">+      nrSamples++;
   6847 </a><a href="#h4-0-1748" id="h4-0-1748" class="i">+    }
   6848 </a><a href="#h4-0-1749" id="h4-0-1749" class="i">+	}
   6849 </a><a href="#h4-0-1750" id="h4-0-1750" class="i">+	// divide by the total number of samples taken, giving us the average sampled irradiance.
   6850 </a><a href="#h4-0-1751" id="h4-0-1751" class="i">+	irradiance = PI * irradiance * (1.0 / float(nrSamples )) ;
   6851 </a><a href="#h4-0-1752" id="h4-0-1752" class="i">+  
   6852 </a><a href="#h4-0-1753" id="h4-0-1753" class="i">+ 
   6853 </a><a href="#h4-0-1754" id="h4-0-1754" class="i">+	gl_FragColor = vec4(irradiance, 1.0);
   6854 </a><a href="#h4-0-1755" id="h4-0-1755" class="i">+}`,Lb=`precision highp float;\r
   6855 </a><a href="#h4-0-1756" id="h4-0-1756" class="i">+varying vec3 localPos;\r
   6856 </a><a href="#h4-0-1757" id="h4-0-1757" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;\r
   6857 </a><a href="#h4-0-1758" id="h4-0-1758" class="i">+\r
   6858 </a><a href="#h4-0-1759" id="h4-0-1759" class="i">+// our texture\r
   6859 </a><a href="#h4-0-1760" id="h4-0-1760" class="i">+uniform sampler2D environmentMap;\r
   6860 </a><a href="#h4-0-1761" id="h4-0-1761" class="i">+uniform float roughness;\r
   6861 </a><a href="#h4-0-1762" id="h4-0-1762" class="i">+\r
   6862 </a><a href="#h4-0-1763" id="h4-0-1763" class="i">+const float PI = 3.14159265359;\r
   6863 </a><a href="#h4-0-1764" id="h4-0-1764" class="i">+\r
   6864 </a><a href="#h4-0-1765" id="h4-0-1765" class="i">+float VanDerCorput(int bits);\r
   6865 </a><a href="#h4-0-1766" id="h4-0-1766" class="i">+vec2 HammersleyNoBitOps(int i, int N);\r
   6866 </a><a href="#h4-0-1767" id="h4-0-1767" class="i">+vec3 ImportanceSampleGGX(vec2 Xi, vec3 N, float roughness);\r
   6867 </a><a href="#h4-0-1768" id="h4-0-1768" class="i">+\r
   6868 </a><a href="#h4-0-1769" id="h4-0-1769" class="i">+\r
   6869 </a><a href="#h4-0-1770" id="h4-0-1770" class="i">+vec2 nTOE( vec3 v ){\r
   6870 </a><a href="#h4-0-1771" id="h4-0-1771" class="i">+  // x = r sin(phi) cos(theta)   \r
   6871 </a><a href="#h4-0-1772" id="h4-0-1772" class="i">+  // y = r cos(phi)  \r
   6872 </a><a href="#h4-0-1773" id="h4-0-1773" class="i">+  // z = r sin(phi) sin(theta)\r
   6873 </a><a href="#h4-0-1774" id="h4-0-1774" class="i">+  float phi = acos( v.y );\r
   6874 </a><a href="#h4-0-1775" id="h4-0-1775" class="i">+  // if phi is 0, then there are no x, z components\r
   6875 </a><a href="#h4-0-1776" id="h4-0-1776" class="i">+  float theta = 0.0;\r
   6876 </a><a href="#h4-0-1777" id="h4-0-1777" class="i">+  // else \r
   6877 </a><a href="#h4-0-1778" id="h4-0-1778" class="i">+  theta = acos(v.x / sin(phi));\r
   6878 </a><a href="#h4-0-1779" id="h4-0-1779" class="i">+  float sinTheta = v.z / sin(phi);\r
   6879 </a><a href="#h4-0-1780" id="h4-0-1780" class="i">+  if (sinTheta &lt; 0.0) {\r
   6880 </a><a href="#h4-0-1781" id="h4-0-1781" class="i">+    // Turn it into -theta, but in the 0-2PI range\r
   6881 </a><a href="#h4-0-1782" id="h4-0-1782" class="i">+    theta = 2.0 * PI - theta;\r
   6882 </a><a href="#h4-0-1783" id="h4-0-1783" class="i">+  }\r
   6883 </a><a href="#h4-0-1784" id="h4-0-1784" class="i">+  theta = theta / (2.0 * 3.14159);\r
   6884 </a><a href="#h4-0-1785" id="h4-0-1785" class="i">+  phi = phi / 3.14159 ;\r
   6885 </a><a href="#h4-0-1786" id="h4-0-1786" class="i">+  \r
   6886 </a><a href="#h4-0-1787" id="h4-0-1787" class="i">+  vec2 angles = vec2( phi, theta );\r
   6887 </a><a href="#h4-0-1788" id="h4-0-1788" class="i">+  return angles;\r
   6888 </a><a href="#h4-0-1789" id="h4-0-1789" class="i">+}\r
   6889 </a><a href="#h4-0-1790" id="h4-0-1790" class="i">+\r
   6890 </a><a href="#h4-0-1791" id="h4-0-1791" class="i">+\r
   6891 </a><a href="#h4-0-1792" id="h4-0-1792" class="i">+void main(){\r
   6892 </a><a href="#h4-0-1793" id="h4-0-1793" class="i">+  const int SAMPLE_COUNT = 400; // 4096\r
   6893 </a><a href="#h4-0-1794" id="h4-0-1794" class="i">+  int lowRoughnessLimit = int(pow(2.0,(roughness+0.1)*20.0));\r
   6894 </a><a href="#h4-0-1795" id="h4-0-1795" class="i">+  float totalWeight = 0.0;\r
   6895 </a><a href="#h4-0-1796" id="h4-0-1796" class="i">+  vec3 prefilteredColor = vec3(0.0);\r
   6896 </a><a href="#h4-0-1797" id="h4-0-1797" class="i">+  float phi = vTexCoord.x * 2.0 * PI;\r
   6897 </a><a href="#h4-0-1798" id="h4-0-1798" class="i">+  float theta = vTexCoord.y * PI;\r
   6898 </a><a href="#h4-0-1799" id="h4-0-1799" class="i">+  float x = sin(theta) * cos(phi);\r
   6899 </a><a href="#h4-0-1800" id="h4-0-1800" class="i">+  float y = sin(theta) * sin(phi);\r
   6900 </a><a href="#h4-0-1801" id="h4-0-1801" class="i">+  float z = cos(theta);\r
   6901 </a><a href="#h4-0-1802" id="h4-0-1802" class="i">+  vec3 N = vec3(x,y,z);\r
   6902 </a><a href="#h4-0-1803" id="h4-0-1803" class="i">+  vec3 V = N;\r
   6903 </a><a href="#h4-0-1804" id="h4-0-1804" class="i">+  for (int i = 0; i &lt; SAMPLE_COUNT; ++i)\r
   6904 </a><a href="#h4-0-1805" id="h4-0-1805" class="i">+  {\r
   6905 </a><a href="#h4-0-1806" id="h4-0-1806" class="i">+    // break at smaller sample numbers for low roughness levels\r
   6906 </a><a href="#h4-0-1807" id="h4-0-1807" class="i">+    if(i == lowRoughnessLimit)\r
   6907 </a><a href="#h4-0-1808" id="h4-0-1808" class="i">+    {\r
   6908 </a><a href="#h4-0-1809" id="h4-0-1809" class="i">+      break;\r
   6909 </a><a href="#h4-0-1810" id="h4-0-1810" class="i">+    }\r
   6910 </a><a href="#h4-0-1811" id="h4-0-1811" class="i">+    vec2 Xi = HammersleyNoBitOps(i, SAMPLE_COUNT);\r
   6911 </a><a href="#h4-0-1812" id="h4-0-1812" class="i">+    vec3 H = ImportanceSampleGGX(Xi, N, roughness);\r
   6912 </a><a href="#h4-0-1813" id="h4-0-1813" class="i">+    vec3 L = normalize(2.0 * dot(V, H) * H - V);\r
   6913 </a><a href="#h4-0-1814" id="h4-0-1814" class="i">+\r
   6914 </a><a href="#h4-0-1815" id="h4-0-1815" class="i">+    float NdotL = max(dot(N, L), 0.0);\r
   6915 </a><a href="#h4-0-1816" id="h4-0-1816" class="i">+    if (NdotL &gt; 0.0)\r
   6916 </a><a href="#h4-0-1817" id="h4-0-1817" class="i">+    {\r
   6917 </a><a href="#h4-0-1818" id="h4-0-1818" class="i">+      prefilteredColor += texture2D(environmentMap, nTOE(L)).xyz * NdotL;\r
   6918 </a><a href="#h4-0-1819" id="h4-0-1819" class="i">+      totalWeight += NdotL;\r
   6919 </a><a href="#h4-0-1820" id="h4-0-1820" class="i">+    }\r
   6920 </a><a href="#h4-0-1821" id="h4-0-1821" class="i">+  }\r
   6921 </a><a href="#h4-0-1822" id="h4-0-1822" class="i">+  prefilteredColor = prefilteredColor / totalWeight;\r
   6922 </a><a href="#h4-0-1823" id="h4-0-1823" class="i">+\r
   6923 </a><a href="#h4-0-1824" id="h4-0-1824" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = vec4(prefilteredColor, 1.0);\r
   6924 </a><a href="#h4-0-1825" id="h4-0-1825" class="i">+}\r
   6925 </a><a href="#h4-0-1826" id="h4-0-1826" class="i">+\r
   6926 </a><a href="#h4-0-1827" id="h4-0-1827" class="i">+vec3 ImportanceSampleGGX(vec2 Xi, vec3 N, float roughness){\r
   6927 </a><a href="#h4-0-1828" id="h4-0-1828" class="i">+  float a = roughness * roughness;\r
   6928 </a><a href="#h4-0-1829" id="h4-0-1829" class="i">+\r
   6929 </a><a href="#h4-0-1830" id="h4-0-1830" class="i">+  float phi = 2.0 * PI * Xi.x;\r
   6930 </a><a href="#h4-0-1831" id="h4-0-1831" class="i">+  float cosTheta = sqrt((1.0 - Xi.y) / (1.0 + (a * a - 1.0) * Xi.y));\r
   6931 </a><a href="#h4-0-1832" id="h4-0-1832" class="i">+  float sinTheta = sqrt(1.0 - cosTheta * cosTheta);\r
   6932 </a><a href="#h4-0-1833" id="h4-0-1833" class="i">+  // from spherical coordinates to cartesian coordinates\r
   6933 </a><a href="#h4-0-1834" id="h4-0-1834" class="i">+  vec3 H;\r
   6934 </a><a href="#h4-0-1835" id="h4-0-1835" class="i">+  H.x = cos(phi) * sinTheta;\r
   6935 </a><a href="#h4-0-1836" id="h4-0-1836" class="i">+  H.y = sin(phi) * sinTheta;\r
   6936 </a><a href="#h4-0-1837" id="h4-0-1837" class="i">+  H.z = cosTheta;\r
   6937 </a><a href="#h4-0-1838" id="h4-0-1838" class="i">+\r
   6938 </a><a href="#h4-0-1839" id="h4-0-1839" class="i">+  // from tangent-space vector to world-space sample vector\r
   6939 </a><a href="#h4-0-1840" id="h4-0-1840" class="i">+  vec3 up = abs(N.z) &lt; 0.999 ? vec3(0.0, 0.0, 1.0) : vec3(1.0, 0.0, 0.0);\r
   6940 </a><a href="#h4-0-1841" id="h4-0-1841" class="i">+  vec3 tangent = normalize(cross(up, N));\r
   6941 </a><a href="#h4-0-1842" id="h4-0-1842" class="i">+  vec3 bitangent = cross(N, tangent);\r
   6942 </a><a href="#h4-0-1843" id="h4-0-1843" class="i">+\r
   6943 </a><a href="#h4-0-1844" id="h4-0-1844" class="i">+  vec3 sampleVec = tangent * H.x + bitangent * H.y + N * H.z;\r
   6944 </a><a href="#h4-0-1845" id="h4-0-1845" class="i">+  return normalize(sampleVec);\r
   6945 </a><a href="#h4-0-1846" id="h4-0-1846" class="i">+}\r
   6946 </a><a href="#h4-0-1847" id="h4-0-1847" class="i">+\r
   6947 </a><a href="#h4-0-1848" id="h4-0-1848" class="i">+\r
   6948 </a><a href="#h4-0-1849" id="h4-0-1849" class="i">+float VanDerCorput(int n, int base)\r
   6949 </a><a href="#h4-0-1850" id="h4-0-1850" class="i">+{\r
   6950 </a><a href="#h4-0-1851" id="h4-0-1851" class="i">+#ifdef WEBGL2\r
   6951 </a><a href="#h4-0-1852" id="h4-0-1852" class="i">+\r
   6952 </a><a href="#h4-0-1853" id="h4-0-1853" class="i">+    uint bits = uint(n);\r
   6953 </a><a href="#h4-0-1854" id="h4-0-1854" class="i">+    bits = (bits &lt;&lt; 16u) | (bits &gt;&gt; 16u);\r
   6954 </a><a href="#h4-0-1855" id="h4-0-1855" class="i">+    bits = ((bits &amp; 0x55555555u) &lt;&lt; 1u) | ((bits &amp; 0xAAAAAAAAu) &gt;&gt; 1u);\r
   6955 </a><a href="#h4-0-1856" id="h4-0-1856" class="i">+    bits = ((bits &amp; 0x33333333u) &lt;&lt; 2u) | ((bits &amp; 0xCCCCCCCCu) &gt;&gt; 2u);\r
   6956 </a><a href="#h4-0-1857" id="h4-0-1857" class="i">+    bits = ((bits &amp; 0x0F0F0F0Fu) &lt;&lt; 4u) | ((bits &amp; 0xF0F0F0F0u) &gt;&gt; 4u);\r
   6957 </a><a href="#h4-0-1858" id="h4-0-1858" class="i">+    bits = ((bits &amp; 0x00FF00FFu) &lt;&lt; 8u) | ((bits &amp; 0xFF00FF00u) &gt;&gt; 8u);\r
   6958 </a><a href="#h4-0-1859" id="h4-0-1859" class="i">+    return float(bits) * 2.3283064365386963e-10; // / 0x100000000\r
   6959 </a><a href="#h4-0-1860" id="h4-0-1860" class="i">+\r
   6960 </a><a href="#h4-0-1861" id="h4-0-1861" class="i">+#else\r
   6961 </a><a href="#h4-0-1862" id="h4-0-1862" class="i">+\r
   6962 </a><a href="#h4-0-1863" id="h4-0-1863" class="i">+  float invBase = 1.0 / float(base);\r
   6963 </a><a href="#h4-0-1864" id="h4-0-1864" class="i">+  float denom = 1.0;\r
   6964 </a><a href="#h4-0-1865" id="h4-0-1865" class="i">+  float result = 0.0;\r
   6965 </a><a href="#h4-0-1866" id="h4-0-1866" class="i">+\r
   6966 </a><a href="#h4-0-1867" id="h4-0-1867" class="i">+\r
   6967 </a><a href="#h4-0-1868" id="h4-0-1868" class="i">+  for (int i = 0; i &lt; 32; ++i)\r
   6968 </a><a href="#h4-0-1869" id="h4-0-1869" class="i">+  {\r
   6969 </a><a href="#h4-0-1870" id="h4-0-1870" class="i">+        if (n &gt; 0)\r
   6970 </a><a href="#h4-0-1871" id="h4-0-1871" class="i">+        {\r
   6971 </a><a href="#h4-0-1872" id="h4-0-1872" class="i">+        denom = mod(float(n), 2.0);\r
   6972 </a><a href="#h4-0-1873" id="h4-0-1873" class="i">+        result += denom * invBase;\r
   6973 </a><a href="#h4-0-1874" id="h4-0-1874" class="i">+        invBase = invBase / 2.0;\r
   6974 </a><a href="#h4-0-1875" id="h4-0-1875" class="i">+        n = int(float(n) / 2.0);\r
   6975 </a><a href="#h4-0-1876" id="h4-0-1876" class="i">+        }\r
   6976 </a><a href="#h4-0-1877" id="h4-0-1877" class="i">+  }\r
   6977 </a><a href="#h4-0-1878" id="h4-0-1878" class="i">+\r
   6978 </a><a href="#h4-0-1879" id="h4-0-1879" class="i">+\r
   6979 </a><a href="#h4-0-1880" id="h4-0-1880" class="i">+  return result;\r
   6980 </a><a href="#h4-0-1881" id="h4-0-1881" class="i">+\r
   6981 </a><a href="#h4-0-1882" id="h4-0-1882" class="i">+#endif\r
   6982 </a><a href="#h4-0-1883" id="h4-0-1883" class="i">+}\r
   6983 </a><a href="#h4-0-1884" id="h4-0-1884" class="i">+\r
   6984 </a><a href="#h4-0-1885" id="h4-0-1885" class="i">+vec2 HammersleyNoBitOps(int i, int N)\r
   6985 </a><a href="#h4-0-1886" id="h4-0-1886" class="i">+{\r
   6986 </a><a href="#h4-0-1887" id="h4-0-1887" class="i">+  return vec2(float(i) / float(N), VanDerCorput(i, 2));\r
   6987 </a><a href="#h4-0-1888" id="h4-0-1888" class="i">+}\r
   6988 </a><a href="#h4-0-1889" id="h4-0-1889" class="i">+`,Dc=`precision highp float;
   6989 </a><a href="#h4-0-1890" id="h4-0-1890" class="i">+
   6990 </a><a href="#h4-0-1891" id="h4-0-1891" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   6991 </a><a href="#h4-0-1892" id="h4-0-1892" class="i">+uniform vec2 canvasSize;
   6992 </a><a href="#h4-0-1893" id="h4-0-1893" class="i">+uniform vec2 texelSize;
   6993 </a><a href="#h4-0-1894" id="h4-0-1894" class="i">+
   6994 </a><a href="#h4-0-1895" id="h4-0-1895" class="i">+IN vec2 vTexCoord;
   6995 </a><a href="#h4-0-1896" id="h4-0-1896" class="i">+
   6996 </a><a href="#h4-0-1897" id="h4-0-1897" class="i">+struct FilterInputs {
   6997 </a><a href="#h4-0-1898" id="h4-0-1898" class="i">+  vec2 texCoord;
   6998 </a><a href="#h4-0-1899" id="h4-0-1899" class="i">+  vec2 canvasSize;
   6999 </a><a href="#h4-0-1900" id="h4-0-1900" class="i">+  vec2 texelSize;
   7000 </a><a href="#h4-0-1901" id="h4-0-1901" class="i">+};
   7001 </a><a href="#h4-0-1902" id="h4-0-1902" class="i">+
   7002 </a><a href="#h4-0-1903" id="h4-0-1903" class="i">+void main(void) {
   7003 </a><a href="#h4-0-1904" id="h4-0-1904" class="i">+  FilterInputs inputs;
   7004 </a><a href="#h4-0-1905" id="h4-0-1905" class="i">+  inputs.texCoord = vTexCoord;
   7005 </a><a href="#h4-0-1906" id="h4-0-1906" class="i">+  inputs.canvasSize = canvasSize;
   7006 </a><a href="#h4-0-1907" id="h4-0-1907" class="i">+  inputs.texelSize = texelSize;
   7007 </a><a href="#h4-0-1908" id="h4-0-1908" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR = HOOK_getColor(inputs, tex0);
   7008 </a><a href="#h4-0-1909" id="h4-0-1909" class="i">+  OUT_COLOR.rgb *= outColor.a;
   7009 </a><a href="#h4-0-1910" id="h4-0-1910" class="i">+}
   7010 </a><a href="#h4-0-1911" id="h4-0-1911" class="i">+`,Fc=`precision highp float;
   7011 </a><a href="#h4-0-1912" id="h4-0-1912" class="i">+
   7012 </a><a href="#h4-0-1913" id="h4-0-1913" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7013 </a><a href="#h4-0-1914" id="h4-0-1914" class="i">+
   7014 </a><a href="#h4-0-1915" id="h4-0-1915" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7015 </a><a href="#h4-0-1916" id="h4-0-1916" class="i">+
   7016 </a><a href="#h4-0-1917" id="h4-0-1917" class="i">+float luma(vec3 color) {
   7017 </a><a href="#h4-0-1918" id="h4-0-1918" class="i">+  // weighted grayscale with luminance values
   7018 </a><a href="#h4-0-1919" id="h4-0-1919" class="i">+  return dot(color, vec3(0.2126, 0.7152, 0.0722));
   7019 </a><a href="#h4-0-1920" id="h4-0-1920" class="i">+}
   7020 </a><a href="#h4-0-1921" id="h4-0-1921" class="i">+
   7021 </a><a href="#h4-0-1922" id="h4-0-1922" class="i">+void main() {
   7022 </a><a href="#h4-0-1923" id="h4-0-1923" class="i">+  vec4 tex = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   7023 </a><a href="#h4-0-1924" id="h4-0-1924" class="i">+  float gray = luma(tex.rgb);
   7024 </a><a href="#h4-0-1925" id="h4-0-1925" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = vec4(gray, gray, gray, tex.a);
   7025 </a><a href="#h4-0-1926" id="h4-0-1926" class="i">+}
   7026 </a><a href="#h4-0-1927" id="h4-0-1927" class="i">+`,Tc=`// Reduces the bright areas in an image
   7027 </a><a href="#h4-0-1928" id="h4-0-1928" class="i">+
   7028 </a><a href="#h4-0-1929" id="h4-0-1929" class="i">+precision highp float;
   7029 </a><a href="#h4-0-1930" id="h4-0-1930" class="i">+
   7030 </a><a href="#h4-0-1931" id="h4-0-1931" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7031 </a><a href="#h4-0-1932" id="h4-0-1932" class="i">+
   7032 </a><a href="#h4-0-1933" id="h4-0-1933" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7033 </a><a href="#h4-0-1934" id="h4-0-1934" class="i">+uniform vec2 texelSize;
   7034 </a><a href="#h4-0-1935" id="h4-0-1935" class="i">+
   7035 </a><a href="#h4-0-1936" id="h4-0-1936" class="i">+float luma(vec3 color) {
   7036 </a><a href="#h4-0-1937" id="h4-0-1937" class="i">+  // weighted grayscale with luminance values
   7037 </a><a href="#h4-0-1938" id="h4-0-1938" class="i">+  // weights 77, 151, 28 taken from src/image/filters.js
   7038 </a><a href="#h4-0-1939" id="h4-0-1939" class="i">+  return dot(color, vec3(0.300781, 0.589844, 0.109375));
   7039 </a><a href="#h4-0-1940" id="h4-0-1940" class="i">+}
   7040 </a><a href="#h4-0-1941" id="h4-0-1941" class="i">+
   7041 </a><a href="#h4-0-1942" id="h4-0-1942" class="i">+void main() {
   7042 </a><a href="#h4-0-1943" id="h4-0-1943" class="i">+  vec4 color = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   7043 </a><a href="#h4-0-1944" id="h4-0-1944" class="i">+  float lum = luma(color.rgb);
   7044 </a><a href="#h4-0-1945" id="h4-0-1945" class="i">+
   7045 </a><a href="#h4-0-1946" id="h4-0-1946" class="i">+  // set current color as the darkest neighbor color
   7046 </a><a href="#h4-0-1947" id="h4-0-1947" class="i">+
   7047 </a><a href="#h4-0-1948" id="h4-0-1948" class="i">+  vec4 neighbors[4];
   7048 </a><a href="#h4-0-1949" id="h4-0-1949" class="i">+  neighbors[0] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2( texelSize.x, 0.0));
   7049 </a><a href="#h4-0-1950" id="h4-0-1950" class="i">+  neighbors[1] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(-texelSize.x, 0.0));
   7050 </a><a href="#h4-0-1951" id="h4-0-1951" class="i">+  neighbors[2] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(0.0,  texelSize.y));
   7051 </a><a href="#h4-0-1952" id="h4-0-1952" class="i">+  neighbors[3] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(0.0, -texelSize.y));
   7052 </a><a href="#h4-0-1953" id="h4-0-1953" class="i">+
   7053 </a><a href="#h4-0-1954" id="h4-0-1954" class="i">+  for (int i = 0; i &lt; 4; i++) {
   7054 </a><a href="#h4-0-1955" id="h4-0-1955" class="i">+    vec4 neighborColor = neighbors[i];
   7055 </a><a href="#h4-0-1956" id="h4-0-1956" class="i">+    float neighborLum = luma(neighborColor.rgb);
   7056 </a><a href="#h4-0-1957" id="h4-0-1957" class="i">+
   7057 </a><a href="#h4-0-1958" id="h4-0-1958" class="i">+    if (neighborLum &lt; lum) {
   7058 </a><a href="#h4-0-1959" id="h4-0-1959" class="i">+      color = neighborColor;
   7059 </a><a href="#h4-0-1960" id="h4-0-1960" class="i">+      lum = neighborLum;
   7060 </a><a href="#h4-0-1961" id="h4-0-1961" class="i">+    }
   7061 </a><a href="#h4-0-1962" id="h4-0-1962" class="i">+  }
   7062 </a><a href="#h4-0-1963" id="h4-0-1963" class="i">+
   7063 </a><a href="#h4-0-1964" id="h4-0-1964" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = color;
   7064 </a><a href="#h4-0-1965" id="h4-0-1965" class="i">+}
   7065 </a><a href="#h4-0-1966" id="h4-0-1966" class="i">+`,Nc=`// Increase the bright areas in an image
   7066 </a><a href="#h4-0-1967" id="h4-0-1967" class="i">+
   7067 </a><a href="#h4-0-1968" id="h4-0-1968" class="i">+precision highp float;
   7068 </a><a href="#h4-0-1969" id="h4-0-1969" class="i">+
   7069 </a><a href="#h4-0-1970" id="h4-0-1970" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7070 </a><a href="#h4-0-1971" id="h4-0-1971" class="i">+
   7071 </a><a href="#h4-0-1972" id="h4-0-1972" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7072 </a><a href="#h4-0-1973" id="h4-0-1973" class="i">+uniform vec2 texelSize;
   7073 </a><a href="#h4-0-1974" id="h4-0-1974" class="i">+
   7074 </a><a href="#h4-0-1975" id="h4-0-1975" class="i">+float luma(vec3 color) {
   7075 </a><a href="#h4-0-1976" id="h4-0-1976" class="i">+  // weighted grayscale with luminance values
   7076 </a><a href="#h4-0-1977" id="h4-0-1977" class="i">+  // weights 77, 151, 28 taken from src/image/filters.js
   7077 </a><a href="#h4-0-1978" id="h4-0-1978" class="i">+  return dot(color, vec3(0.300781, 0.589844, 0.109375));
   7078 </a><a href="#h4-0-1979" id="h4-0-1979" class="i">+}
   7079 </a><a href="#h4-0-1980" id="h4-0-1980" class="i">+
   7080 </a><a href="#h4-0-1981" id="h4-0-1981" class="i">+void main() {
   7081 </a><a href="#h4-0-1982" id="h4-0-1982" class="i">+  vec4 color = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   7082 </a><a href="#h4-0-1983" id="h4-0-1983" class="i">+  float lum = luma(color.rgb);
   7083 </a><a href="#h4-0-1984" id="h4-0-1984" class="i">+
   7084 </a><a href="#h4-0-1985" id="h4-0-1985" class="i">+  // set current color as the brightest neighbor color
   7085 </a><a href="#h4-0-1986" id="h4-0-1986" class="i">+
   7086 </a><a href="#h4-0-1987" id="h4-0-1987" class="i">+  vec4 neighbors[4];
   7087 </a><a href="#h4-0-1988" id="h4-0-1988" class="i">+  neighbors[0] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2( texelSize.x, 0.0));
   7088 </a><a href="#h4-0-1989" id="h4-0-1989" class="i">+  neighbors[1] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(-texelSize.x, 0.0));
   7089 </a><a href="#h4-0-1990" id="h4-0-1990" class="i">+  neighbors[2] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(0.0,  texelSize.y));
   7090 </a><a href="#h4-0-1991" id="h4-0-1991" class="i">+  neighbors[3] = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord + vec2(0.0, -texelSize.y));
   7091 </a><a href="#h4-0-1992" id="h4-0-1992" class="i">+
   7092 </a><a href="#h4-0-1993" id="h4-0-1993" class="i">+  for (int i = 0; i &lt; 4; i++) {
   7093 </a><a href="#h4-0-1994" id="h4-0-1994" class="i">+    vec4 neighborColor = neighbors[i];
   7094 </a><a href="#h4-0-1995" id="h4-0-1995" class="i">+    float neighborLum = luma(neighborColor.rgb);
   7095 </a><a href="#h4-0-1996" id="h4-0-1996" class="i">+
   7096 </a><a href="#h4-0-1997" id="h4-0-1997" class="i">+    if (neighborLum &gt; lum) {
   7097 </a><a href="#h4-0-1998" id="h4-0-1998" class="i">+      color = neighborColor;
   7098 </a><a href="#h4-0-1999" id="h4-0-1999" class="i">+      lum = neighborLum;
   7099 </a><a href="#h4-0-2000" id="h4-0-2000" class="i">+    }
   7100 </a><a href="#h4-0-2001" id="h4-0-2001" class="i">+  }
   7101 </a><a href="#h4-0-2002" id="h4-0-2002" class="i">+
   7102 </a><a href="#h4-0-2003" id="h4-0-2003" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = color;
   7103 </a><a href="#h4-0-2004" id="h4-0-2004" class="i">+}
   7104 </a><a href="#h4-0-2005" id="h4-0-2005" class="i">+`,Ic=`precision highp float;
   7105 </a><a href="#h4-0-2006" id="h4-0-2006" class="i">+
   7106 </a><a href="#h4-0-2007" id="h4-0-2007" class="i">+// Two-pass blur filter, unweighted kernel.
   7107 </a><a href="#h4-0-2008" id="h4-0-2008" class="i">+// See also a similar blur at Adam Ferriss&#39; repo of shader examples:
   7108 </a><a href="#h4-0-2009" id="h4-0-2009" class="i">+// https://github.com/aferriss/p5jsShaderExamples/blob/gh-pages/4_image-effects/4-9_single-pass-blur/effect.frag
   7109 </a><a href="#h4-0-2010" id="h4-0-2010" class="i">+
   7110 </a><a href="#h4-0-2011" id="h4-0-2011" class="i">+
   7111 </a><a href="#h4-0-2012" id="h4-0-2012" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7112 </a><a href="#h4-0-2013" id="h4-0-2013" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7113 </a><a href="#h4-0-2014" id="h4-0-2014" class="i">+uniform vec2 direction;
   7114 </a><a href="#h4-0-2015" id="h4-0-2015" class="i">+uniform vec2 canvasSize;
   7115 </a><a href="#h4-0-2016" id="h4-0-2016" class="i">+uniform float radius;
   7116 </a><a href="#h4-0-2017" id="h4-0-2017" class="i">+
   7117 </a><a href="#h4-0-2018" id="h4-0-2018" class="i">+float random(vec2 p) {
   7118 </a><a href="#h4-0-2019" id="h4-0-2019" class="i">+  vec3 p3  = fract(vec3(p.xyx) * .1031);
   7119 </a><a href="#h4-0-2020" id="h4-0-2020" class="i">+  p3 += dot(p3, p3.yzx + 33.33);
   7120 </a><a href="#h4-0-2021" id="h4-0-2021" class="i">+  return fract((p3.x + p3.y) * p3.z);
   7121 </a><a href="#h4-0-2022" id="h4-0-2022" class="i">+}
   7122 </a><a href="#h4-0-2023" id="h4-0-2023" class="i">+
   7123 </a><a href="#h4-0-2024" id="h4-0-2024" class="i">+// This isn&#39;t a real Gaussian weight, it&#39;s a quadratic weight. It&#39;s what the
   7124 </a><a href="#h4-0-2025" id="h4-0-2025" class="i">+// CPU mode&#39;s blur uses though, so we also use it here to match.
   7125 </a><a href="#h4-0-2026" id="h4-0-2026" class="i">+float quadWeight(float x, float e) {
   7126 </a><a href="#h4-0-2027" id="h4-0-2027" class="i">+  return pow(e-abs(x), 2.);
   7127 </a><a href="#h4-0-2028" id="h4-0-2028" class="i">+}
   7128 </a><a href="#h4-0-2029" id="h4-0-2029" class="i">+
   7129 </a><a href="#h4-0-2030" id="h4-0-2030" class="i">+void main(){
   7130 </a><a href="#h4-0-2031" id="h4-0-2031" class="i">+  vec2 uv = vTexCoord;
   7131 </a><a href="#h4-0-2032" id="h4-0-2032" class="i">+
   7132 </a><a href="#h4-0-2033" id="h4-0-2033" class="i">+  // A reasonable maximum number of samples
   7133 </a><a href="#h4-0-2034" id="h4-0-2034" class="i">+  const float maxSamples = 64.0;
   7134 </a><a href="#h4-0-2035" id="h4-0-2035" class="i">+
   7135 </a><a href="#h4-0-2036" id="h4-0-2036" class="i">+  float numSamples = floor(7. * radius);
   7136 </a><a href="#h4-0-2037" id="h4-0-2037" class="i">+  if (fract(numSamples / 2.) == 0.) {
   7137 </a><a href="#h4-0-2038" id="h4-0-2038" class="i">+    numSamples++;
   7138 </a><a href="#h4-0-2039" id="h4-0-2039" class="i">+  }
   7139 </a><a href="#h4-0-2040" id="h4-0-2040" class="i">+  vec4 avg = vec4(0.0);
   7140 </a><a href="#h4-0-2041" id="h4-0-2041" class="i">+  float total = 0.0;
   7141 </a><a href="#h4-0-2042" id="h4-0-2042" class="i">+
   7142 </a><a href="#h4-0-2043" id="h4-0-2043" class="i">+  // Calculate the spacing to avoid skewing if numSamples &gt; maxSamples
   7143 </a><a href="#h4-0-2044" id="h4-0-2044" class="i">+  float spacing = 1.0;
   7144 </a><a href="#h4-0-2045" id="h4-0-2045" class="i">+  if (numSamples &gt; maxSamples) {
   7145 </a><a href="#h4-0-2046" id="h4-0-2046" class="i">+    spacing = numSamples / maxSamples;
   7146 </a><a href="#h4-0-2047" id="h4-0-2047" class="i">+    numSamples = maxSamples;
   7147 </a><a href="#h4-0-2048" id="h4-0-2048" class="i">+  }
   7148 </a><a href="#h4-0-2049" id="h4-0-2049" class="i">+
   7149 </a><a href="#h4-0-2050" id="h4-0-2050" class="i">+  float randomOffset = (spacing - 1.0) * mix(-0.5, 0.5, random(gl_FragCoord.xy));
   7150 </a><a href="#h4-0-2051" id="h4-0-2051" class="i">+  for (float i = 0.0; i &lt; maxSamples; i++) {
   7151 </a><a href="#h4-0-2052" id="h4-0-2052" class="i">+    if (i &gt;= numSamples) break;
   7152 </a><a href="#h4-0-2053" id="h4-0-2053" class="i">+
   7153 </a><a href="#h4-0-2054" id="h4-0-2054" class="i">+    float sample = i * spacing - (numSamples - 1.0) * 0.5 * spacing + randomOffset;
   7154 </a><a href="#h4-0-2055" id="h4-0-2055" class="i">+    vec2 sampleCoord = uv + vec2(sample, sample) / canvasSize * direction;
   7155 </a><a href="#h4-0-2056" id="h4-0-2056" class="i">+    float weight = quadWeight(sample, (numSamples - 1.0) * 0.5 * spacing);
   7156 </a><a href="#h4-0-2057" id="h4-0-2057" class="i">+
   7157 </a><a href="#h4-0-2058" id="h4-0-2058" class="i">+    avg += weight * texture2D(tex0, sampleCoord);
   7158 </a><a href="#h4-0-2059" id="h4-0-2059" class="i">+    total += weight;
   7159 </a><a href="#h4-0-2060" id="h4-0-2060" class="i">+  }
   7160 </a><a href="#h4-0-2061" id="h4-0-2061" class="i">+
   7161 </a><a href="#h4-0-2062" id="h4-0-2062" class="i">+  avg /= total;
   7162 </a><a href="#h4-0-2063" id="h4-0-2063" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = avg;
   7163 </a><a href="#h4-0-2064" id="h4-0-2064" class="i">+}
   7164 </a><a href="#h4-0-2065" id="h4-0-2065" class="i">+`,kc=`// Limit color space for a stylized cartoon / poster effect
   7165 </a><a href="#h4-0-2066" id="h4-0-2066" class="i">+
   7166 </a><a href="#h4-0-2067" id="h4-0-2067" class="i">+precision highp float;
   7167 </a><a href="#h4-0-2068" id="h4-0-2068" class="i">+
   7168 </a><a href="#h4-0-2069" id="h4-0-2069" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7169 </a><a href="#h4-0-2070" id="h4-0-2070" class="i">+
   7170 </a><a href="#h4-0-2071" id="h4-0-2071" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7171 </a><a href="#h4-0-2072" id="h4-0-2072" class="i">+uniform float filterParameter;
   7172 </a><a href="#h4-0-2073" id="h4-0-2073" class="i">+
   7173 </a><a href="#h4-0-2074" id="h4-0-2074" class="i">+vec3 quantize(vec3 color, float n) {
   7174 </a><a href="#h4-0-2075" id="h4-0-2075" class="i">+  // restrict values to N options/bins
   7175 </a><a href="#h4-0-2076" id="h4-0-2076" class="i">+  // and floor each channel to nearest value
   7176 </a><a href="#h4-0-2077" id="h4-0-2077" class="i">+  //
   7177 </a><a href="#h4-0-2078" id="h4-0-2078" class="i">+  // eg. when N = 5, values = 0.0, 0.25, 0.50, 0.75, 1.0
   7178 </a><a href="#h4-0-2079" id="h4-0-2079" class="i">+  // then quantize (0.1, 0.7, 0.9) -&gt; (0.0, 0.5, 1.0)
   7179 </a><a href="#h4-0-2080" id="h4-0-2080" class="i">+
   7180 </a><a href="#h4-0-2081" id="h4-0-2081" class="i">+  color = color * n;
   7181 </a><a href="#h4-0-2082" id="h4-0-2082" class="i">+  color = floor(color);
   7182 </a><a href="#h4-0-2083" id="h4-0-2083" class="i">+  color = color / (n - 1.0);
   7183 </a><a href="#h4-0-2084" id="h4-0-2084" class="i">+  return color;
   7184 </a><a href="#h4-0-2085" id="h4-0-2085" class="i">+}
   7185 </a><a href="#h4-0-2086" id="h4-0-2086" class="i">+
   7186 </a><a href="#h4-0-2087" id="h4-0-2087" class="i">+void main() {
   7187 </a><a href="#h4-0-2088" id="h4-0-2088" class="i">+  vec4 color = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   7188 </a><a href="#h4-0-2089" id="h4-0-2089" class="i">+
   7189 </a><a href="#h4-0-2090" id="h4-0-2090" class="i">+  vec3 restrictedColor = quantize(color.rgb / color.a, filterParameter);
   7190 </a><a href="#h4-0-2091" id="h4-0-2091" class="i">+
   7191 </a><a href="#h4-0-2092" id="h4-0-2092" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = vec4(restrictedColor.rgb * color.a, color.a);
   7192 </a><a href="#h4-0-2093" id="h4-0-2093" class="i">+}
   7193 </a><a href="#h4-0-2094" id="h4-0-2094" class="i">+`,Mc=`// Set alpha channel to entirely opaque
   7194 </a><a href="#h4-0-2095" id="h4-0-2095" class="i">+
   7195 </a><a href="#h4-0-2096" id="h4-0-2096" class="i">+precision highp float;
   7196 </a><a href="#h4-0-2097" id="h4-0-2097" class="i">+
   7197 </a><a href="#h4-0-2098" id="h4-0-2098" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7198 </a><a href="#h4-0-2099" id="h4-0-2099" class="i">+
   7199 </a><a href="#h4-0-2100" id="h4-0-2100" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7200 </a><a href="#h4-0-2101" id="h4-0-2101" class="i">+
   7201 </a><a href="#h4-0-2102" id="h4-0-2102" class="i">+void main() {
   7202 </a><a href="#h4-0-2103" id="h4-0-2103" class="i">+  vec4 color = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   7203 </a><a href="#h4-0-2104" id="h4-0-2104" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = vec4(color.rgb / color.a, 1.0);
   7204 </a><a href="#h4-0-2105" id="h4-0-2105" class="i">+}
   7205 </a><a href="#h4-0-2106" id="h4-0-2106" class="i">+`,Lc=`// Set each pixel to inverse value
   7206 </a><a href="#h4-0-2107" id="h4-0-2107" class="i">+// Note that original INVERT does not change the opacity, so this follows suit
   7207 </a><a href="#h4-0-2108" id="h4-0-2108" class="i">+
   7208 </a><a href="#h4-0-2109" id="h4-0-2109" class="i">+precision highp float;
   7209 </a><a href="#h4-0-2110" id="h4-0-2110" class="i">+
   7210 </a><a href="#h4-0-2111" id="h4-0-2111" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7211 </a><a href="#h4-0-2112" id="h4-0-2112" class="i">+
   7212 </a><a href="#h4-0-2113" id="h4-0-2113" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7213 </a><a href="#h4-0-2114" id="h4-0-2114" class="i">+
   7214 </a><a href="#h4-0-2115" id="h4-0-2115" class="i">+void main() {
   7215 </a><a href="#h4-0-2116" id="h4-0-2116" class="i">+vec4 color = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   7216 </a><a href="#h4-0-2117" id="h4-0-2117" class="i">+vec3 origColor = color.rgb / color.a;
   7217 </a><a href="#h4-0-2118" id="h4-0-2118" class="i">+vec3 invertedColor = vec3(1.0) - origColor;
   7218 </a><a href="#h4-0-2119" id="h4-0-2119" class="i">+gl_FragColor = vec4(invertedColor * color.a, color.a);
   7219 </a><a href="#h4-0-2120" id="h4-0-2120" class="i">+}
   7220 </a><a href="#h4-0-2121" id="h4-0-2121" class="i">+`,Rc=`// Convert pixels to either white or black, 
   7221 </a><a href="#h4-0-2122" id="h4-0-2122" class="i">+// depending on if their luma is above or below filterParameter
   7222 </a><a href="#h4-0-2123" id="h4-0-2123" class="i">+
   7223 </a><a href="#h4-0-2124" id="h4-0-2124" class="i">+precision highp float;
   7224 </a><a href="#h4-0-2125" id="h4-0-2125" class="i">+
   7225 </a><a href="#h4-0-2126" id="h4-0-2126" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7226 </a><a href="#h4-0-2127" id="h4-0-2127" class="i">+
   7227 </a><a href="#h4-0-2128" id="h4-0-2128" class="i">+uniform sampler2D tex0;
   7228 </a><a href="#h4-0-2129" id="h4-0-2129" class="i">+uniform float filterParameter;
   7229 </a><a href="#h4-0-2130" id="h4-0-2130" class="i">+
   7230 </a><a href="#h4-0-2131" id="h4-0-2131" class="i">+float luma(vec3 color) {
   7231 </a><a href="#h4-0-2132" id="h4-0-2132" class="i">+  // weighted grayscale with luminance values
   7232 </a><a href="#h4-0-2133" id="h4-0-2133" class="i">+  return dot(color, vec3(0.2126, 0.7152, 0.0722));
   7233 </a><a href="#h4-0-2134" id="h4-0-2134" class="i">+}
   7234 </a><a href="#h4-0-2135" id="h4-0-2135" class="i">+
   7235 </a><a href="#h4-0-2136" id="h4-0-2136" class="i">+void main() {
   7236 </a><a href="#h4-0-2137" id="h4-0-2137" class="i">+  vec4 color = texture2D(tex0, vTexCoord);
   7237 </a><a href="#h4-0-2138" id="h4-0-2138" class="i">+  float gray = luma(color.rgb / color.a);
   7238 </a><a href="#h4-0-2139" id="h4-0-2139" class="i">+  // floor() used to match src/image/filters.js
   7239 </a><a href="#h4-0-2140" id="h4-0-2140" class="i">+  float threshold = floor(filterParameter * 255.0) / 255.0;
   7240 </a><a href="#h4-0-2141" id="h4-0-2141" class="i">+  float blackOrWhite = step(threshold, gray);
   7241 </a><a href="#h4-0-2142" id="h4-0-2142" class="i">+  gl_FragColor = vec4(vec3(blackOrWhite) * color.a, color.a);
   7242 </a><a href="#h4-0-2143" id="h4-0-2143" class="i">+}
   7243 </a><a href="#h4-0-2144" id="h4-0-2144" class="i">+`,Bc=`uniform mat4 uModelViewMatrix;
   7244 </a><a href="#h4-0-2145" id="h4-0-2145" class="i">+uniform mat4 uProjectionMatrix;
   7245 </a><a href="#h4-0-2146" id="h4-0-2146" class="i">+
   7246 </a><a href="#h4-0-2147" id="h4-0-2147" class="i">+attribute vec3 aPosition;
   7247 </a><a href="#h4-0-2148" id="h4-0-2148" class="i">+// texcoords only come from p5 to vertex shader
   7248 </a><a href="#h4-0-2149" id="h4-0-2149" class="i">+// so pass texcoords on to the fragment shader in a varying variable
   7249 </a><a href="#h4-0-2150" id="h4-0-2150" class="i">+attribute vec2 aTexCoord;
   7250 </a><a href="#h4-0-2151" id="h4-0-2151" class="i">+varying vec2 vTexCoord;
   7251 </a><a href="#h4-0-2152" id="h4-0-2152" class="i">+
   7252 </a><a href="#h4-0-2153" id="h4-0-2153" class="i">+void main() {
   7253 </a><a href="#h4-0-2154" id="h4-0-2154" class="i">+  // transferring texcoords for the frag shader
   7254 </a><a href="#h4-0-2155" id="h4-0-2155" class="i">+  vTexCoord = aTexCoord;
   7255 </a><a href="#h4-0-2156" id="h4-0-2156" class="i">+
   7256 </a><a href="#h4-0-2157" id="h4-0-2157" class="i">+  // copy position with a fourth coordinate for projection (1.0 is normal)
   7257 </a><a href="#h4-0-2158" id="h4-0-2158" class="i">+  vec4 positionVec4 = vec4(aPosition, 1.0);
   7258 </a><a href="#h4-0-2159" id="h4-0-2159" class="i">+
   7259 </a><a href="#h4-0-2160" id="h4-0-2160" class="i">+  gl_Position = uProjectionMatrix * uModelViewMatrix * positionVec4;
   7260 </a><a href="#h4-0-2161" id="h4-0-2161" class="i">+}
   7261 </a><a href="#h4-0-2162" id="h4-0-2162" class="i">+`,Gm={},zm={},tl=&quot;&quot;,Pc=function(i,t){tl+=`#define STROKE_CAP_${i} ${t}
   7262 </a><a href="#h4-0-2163" id="h4-0-2163" class="i">+`,Gm[gr[i]]=t},Oc=function(i,t){tl+=`#define STROKE_JOIN_${i} ${t}
   7263 </a><a href="#h4-0-2164" id="h4-0-2164" class="i">+`,zm[gr[i]]=t};Pc(&quot;ROUND&quot;,0);Pc(&quot;PROJECT&quot;,1);Pc(&quot;SQUARE&quot;,2);Oc(&quot;ROUND&quot;,0);Oc(&quot;MITER&quot;,1);Oc(&quot;BEVEL&quot;,2);var lt={normalVert:vb,normalFrag:xb,basicFrag:bb,sphereMappingFrag:_b,lightVert:Um+wb,lightTextureFrag:Cb,phongVert:Eb,phongFrag:Um+Sb,fontVert:Ab,fontFrag:Db,lineVert:tl+Fb,lineFrag:tl+Tb,pointVert:Nb,pointFrag:Ib,imageLightVert:kb,imageLightDiffusedFrag:Mb,imageLightSpecularFrag:Lb,filterBaseVert:Ac,filterBaseFrag:Dc},Rb=lt.sphereMappingFrag;for(let i in lt)lt[i]=ol+lt[i];var Bb={[Ca]:Fc,[Da]:Tc,[Aa]:Nc,[di]:Ic,[xn]:kc,[Ea]:Mc,[Sa]:Lc,[vn]:Rc},Le=class i extends ke{constructor(t,r,n,s,a,o){super(t,r,n,s),this.canvas=this.elt=a||document.createElement(&quot;canvas&quot;),this._setAttributeDefaults(t),this._initContext(),this.GL=this.drawingContext,this._isMainCanvas?(this._pInst._curElement=this,this._pInst.canvas=this.canvas):this.canvas.style.display=&quot;none&quot;,this.elt.id=&quot;defaultCanvas0&quot;,this.elt.classList.add(&quot;p5Canvas&quot;),this.wrappedElt=new
